(30, 1, '2019-12-02 20:35:55', '2019-12-02 20:35:55', '<!-- wp:image {"id":323,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/pexels-photo-2294354.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-323"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Being overweight can lead to diabetes or make it worse.&nbsp; Strengthen your body and melt your love handles with these five easy movements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>&nbsp;1. Curing upright abdominals:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;This standing exercise strengthens the muscles that help your back support the extra weight in your belly.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Stand with your feet aligned with your hips. Keeping your neck, shoulders, and arms relaxed, tuck the muscles in your abdomen and contract them.&nbsp; Imagine a belt tightening around your abdomen. Hold the position for 60 seconds while breathing normally.&nbsp; Do this three times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>&nbsp;2. The gluteal muscle:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Strengthen the humble but powerful muscles that make up your buttocks and are involved in almost every movement you make.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Stand straight with your feet lined up with your hips, arms around your sides, and your shoulders relaxed. Rinse your buttocks as much as possible, tuck your belly and move your right leg about five centimeters behind you by lifting your foot.&nbsp; from the floor. Hold the position for 10 seconds, then change your leg.&nbsp; Do at least three repetitions with each leg.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>&nbsp;3. Dry swimming:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Strengthens the lower back and muscles along the lower part of the spine to improve posture and prevent lower back pain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Lie on your stomach on a carpet with your arms and legs lined up, as if you were Superman. Keep your neck relaxed, head down, stretch your abdominal muscles, then lift your right arm and your left leg for a second.&nbsp; Slowly bring both limbs to the floor and repeat the exercise with the other arm and the other leg.&nbsp; Continue "swimming" for 30 seconds, three times with each leg.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>&nbsp;4. Raised leg:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Like a normal crunch, except that this exercise uses the abdominal muscles.&nbsp; It is less intense and does not require lifting the head off the ground, which could force your neck.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Lie on your back, knees bent, feet flat on the floor, hands behind your head and elbows on the sides.Inspire and contract your abdominal muscles so that the bottom of your back touches the ground, then lift&nbsp; your right foot about three inches off the ground.Hold the position for four seconds, then exhale while lowering the foot to the floor for another four seconds.&nbsp; Repeat with the left leg.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>&nbsp;5. The sweet hundred:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Strengthens the trunk muscles, the abdominals, lower back muscles and those attached to the spine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Lie on your back, your legs together and your knees at a 90-degree angle.&nbsp; Inhale and raise your arms to the ceiling without lifting your shoulders off the floor. When exhaling, relax your torso so as to lift the upper portion of your shoulders.&nbsp; Simultaneously, lower your arms and hold them close to your hips. Contract your abs and begin to raise and lower your arms as if you were using an air pump.&nbsp; Repeat this pump movement 100 times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;One way to fight diabetes is to keep fit and lose weight.&nbsp; These easy exercises that you can do at home will put you on the right track.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '5 easy trunk exercises to fight diabetes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '5-easy-trunk-exercises-to-fight-diabetes', '', '', '2020-01-20 15:06:48', '2020-01-20 15:06:48', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=30', 0, 'post', '', 0),
