(413, 1, '2020-01-20 15:23:05', '2020-01-20 15:23:05', '<!-- wp:image {"id":415,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/disease-4392168_1280-1024x682.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-415"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the majority of cases, the manifestations of allergy are limited to the site of aggression of the allergen (nose, eyes, lungs, skin) and do not put life in danger. But sometimes, they may require care.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In allergy, the range of symptoms is wide and often confusing because all organs are likely to be concerned. Allergens can enter the body in three ways: cutaneous, respiratory or digestive. The reactions are mostly local. If they are generalized, rapid support is needed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The local reactions, very variable, are manifested with an intensity that changes a lot from one person to another. They can even change over time, in the sense of improvement, or on the contrary, an aggravation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Runny nose</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A few grains of pollen in suspension are enough to trigger, in predisposed people, bursts of sneezing as irrepressible as explosive. In severe cases, these bursts follow one another 10 to 30 times in succession and are repeated in crises. This is to say if one can feel a state of fatigue and exhaustion at the end of these mini-earthquakes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Often morning sneeze is associated with itching in the area of ​​the nose and throat and a runny nose. It is truly an avalanche of clear liquid, similar to water, which can not be mistaken for a viral cold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stuffy and/or itchy nose is also characteristic of an allergic cold. Nasal obstruction, sometimes of both nostrils, is due to swelling of the mucosa and secretions. The permanent impression of nasal congestion can be painful, especially at night.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The eyes that cry</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hay fever is very often accompanied by inflammation of the eyes. It is conjunctivitis of allergic origin. The eyes are irritated, giving the impression of having sand under the eyelids. And that’s not all. The intense tingling and the burning sensation are the source of unbearable itching, followed by active scratching sessions. Suddenly, the eyelids begin to swell and the whiteness of the eye turns red. To crown this feverish gaze, the eyes constantly appear on the brink of tears and can no longer stand the light.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At more chronic exposures to allergens (animal hair, dust mites, molds), the symptoms are less intense, but not less painful: tearing, red eyes and eyelids stuck in the morning, eyelashes torn off from rub the eyes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Itchy mouth or skin</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The skin and pulp of certain fruits or vegetables (apple, pear, cherry, peach, tomatoes, carrots …), as well as some spices (paprika, curry …), can, as soon as they are ingested, cause itching of the mouth and the throat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eczematous skin, on the other hand, itches terribly. To the touch, the surface of the lesions caused by eczema is reminiscent of granite. Vesicles – tiny blisters filled with a clear liquid – are formed and the liquid released when scratching then flows over the surface of the lesion, then dries forming small crusts. Note that recent eczema lesions are often preceded by itching. After the acute stage, the redness fades,