(105, 1, '2019-12-03 10:05:13', '2019-12-03 10:05:13', '<!-- wp:image {"id":339,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/pexels-photo-2294361-1.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-339"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; Following an illness or injury, it is important to regain strength in your body. &nbsp;With these 8 easy exercises, you will redevelop strong legs in no time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;The equipment you will need</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;These gentle leg exercises are not only effective if you are recovering from an illness, but also if you just need a boost of activity. &nbsp;You''ll need :</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Light to medium dumbbells A towel A pillow A support chair A space against a wall.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;1. Extension of the seated leg</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: quadriceps Sit on a chair with your feet flat on the floor and stand beside the seat to support you, slowly lift your left leg until it is directly in front of you. &nbsp;one to two seconds, then slowly lower your leg.Repeat with the other leg.Make a series of 10 alternating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;2. Bending of the standing legs</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: strong hamstringsFront to a wall, feet spread to the width of your hips, place your hands against the wall to support you Keep your back straight, slowly bend your right leg at the knee, elevate &nbsp;your heel to your buttocks until your shin is parallel to the ground Hold for two seconds, then return to the starting position Change your leg Make a series of 10 alternating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;3. Walking and pendulum</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: legs, buttocks and backHold with your left hand on your hip and your other hand on the back of a chair or the top of a table as a support guide Raise your left knee up &nbsp;your thigh is parallel to the ground, with the foot flexed, stiffen your left leg, pressing the heel forward and towards the ground while tilting your torso slightly backwards Return to the position of the raised knee &nbsp;then straighten your left leg behind you, leaning forward with your chest, Change your leg, Do a series of 10 alternately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;4. Walking on tiptoe</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: strengthening your calvesBe standing behind a chair, your feet spread to the width of your hips and a hand planted on the chair for support; Using the muscles of your calves, slowly lift yourself on your toes as high as &nbsp;possible without discomfort, hold, then slowly lower your heels to the ground, make a series of 10.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;5. Figure 4 sitting</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: gluteal muscles, lower back, and hips Sit on a chair with your feet flat on the ground. Cross your right ankle on your left knee so your calf is parallel to the ground and your right knee is facing &nbsp;right, keep your back straight, lean forward from the hips until you feel a deep muscle stretch in your right buttock, change legs, make a series of 10.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;6. Hamstring stretches</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: HamstringSlide on your back with your knees bent and both feet flat on the floor, Raise your right leg to the ceiling, then join hands around the back of your right thigh and pull &nbsp;gently to your chest (use a towel if you can not reach it) Change your leg Make a series of 10</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;7. Seated calf stretch</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: calves Sit on the edge of a chair, with the left foot flat on the ground and the right leg extended with the foot flexed, wrap a towel around the ball of your right foot and, keeping your back straight &nbsp;, gently pull your foot toward you as far as possible without discomfort, change your leg, make a series of 10.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;8. Knee drop</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Good for: groin and inner thighsSlide on a floor mat (or, if you want more comfort, on a bed), knees bent and feet flat; Place your hands inside &nbsp;your knees and gently let your knees fall to the floor or bed; gently press to push the stretch as much as possible without discomfort; hold, release, and then repeat; do a series of 10.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'easy toys to strengthen legs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'easy-toys-to-strengthen-legs', '', '', '2020-01-20 15:06:49', '2020-01-20 15:06:49', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=105', 0, 'post', '', 0),
