(173, 1, '2019-12-05 21:10:17', '2019-12-05 21:10:17', '<!-- wp:image {"id":170,"width":551,"height":367,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/240_F_239029065_839Wlk9Jr11ED1RYQsNZIVKBWJLyI3dH.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-170" width="551" height="367"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; Repeat them three times a week and in a short time you will feel invincible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>The back is important</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":172,"width":543,"height":362,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/pexels-photo-1092883.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-172" width="543" height="362"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; Whether you are exercising, carrying a sleeping child, or sitting for long hours, it is essential to have a strong back that gives you the support and mobility you need. It is, however, a part of the body that is often neglected to be trained, largely because one exercises in front of a mirror and the front is seen in it. By toning your back muscles, you will look better, have a better posture, be better protected against back pain or other painful and healthier injuries. The exercises offered here will allow you to work the top, middle and lower back.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Preparation</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>You will need:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; An exercise mat or a thick towel and a pair of dumbbells of two to four kilograms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Before you begin:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; Warm up for three minutes while taking a brisk walk or jumping from one foot to the other. Then, feet apart a distance equal to the width of your hips and knees slightly bent, lift your arms to the sides and gently squeeze the shoulder blades to bring them closer together. Isolate the movement in the middle of the back and avoid waving the arms; your shoulders should only move about 3 centimeters. Repeat a minute.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->\n<h5>Routine:</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Start with two sets of each of the three exercises proposed; when you have gained strength, you can move on to three sets. At the end of each session, gently stretch the muscles you have worked for a few minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Sweater</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Targeted regions: upper back, torso sides, back of shoulders, back of arms.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;A. Lie on your back. Raise your arms towards the ceiling by holding the dumbbells firmly, which should be in alignment with your chest. Flex your legs, knees pointing up, feet flat on the floor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B. Contract the abdominals and lower your arms behind you, without moving them away from your head and holding your elbows slightly bent.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>C. When they are approximately parallel to the ground, return to the starting position. Do 8 to 12 repetitions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Super heroines</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Targeted regions: middle and lower back, buttocks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A. Lie on your stomach, arms outstretched in front, legs straight, instep against the floor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>B. In one motion, lift your feet, arms, and shoulders, contracting the muscles in your lower back. Avoid jerking and do not raise your head when you raise your arms; your neck should be in alignment with the rest of your column.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>C. Hold two seconds and return to the starting position. Do 12 to 15 repetitions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Clenching of the shoulder blades</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Requested regions: middle of the back, back of the shoulders (As a bonus: the strengthening of the muscles of the middle of the back improves the sitting and standing posture.The silhouette is refined.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A. Take the dumbbells and take a step forward, knees bent. Your right foot (front) must be flat on the ground; lift the left heel, keeping on the front part of the sole of the foot. (For the second series, you will reverse the position of the feet.) Lean down flexing, contracted abdominals, right column and neck in the back alignment. Let your arms hang, keeping your hands in line with your shoulders, palms facing backwards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;B. Contract the abs and use the muscles in the middle of your back to squeeze the shoulder blades together and down. Flex your arms, raise your elbows, bringing them back; avoid bringing your shoulders closer to your ears. Your neck should stay in alignment with your spine, your hands in your arms, without breaking at the wrists; your palms are facing backwards. Keep the abs contracted for the duration of the exercise.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>C. Resume the starting position. Do 8 to 12 repetitions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'movements to strengthen your back', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '167-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-12-05 21:10:17', '2019-12-05 21:10:17', '', 