(474, 1, '2020-02-22 12:08:56', '2020-02-22 12:08:56', '<!-- wp:image {"id":486,"width":406,"height":365,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1582372510159.png" alt="" class="wp-image-486" width="406" height="365"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bloating is one of the most annoying stomach problems, familiar to many people around the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The description of this disease in people can vary, but the main concern is always the same including the feeling of increased pressure in the abdomen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It can be associated with many other stomach problems like irritable bowel syndrome, but it can happen independently after a heavy meal or with a poor diet.&nbsp;We are always trying to provide you with the best ways to maintain your health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, here are 10 ways to save yourself from bloating and its annoying pain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":488,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/wrong-check-symbols_1176-335.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-488"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can prevent bloating by eating more slowly and in smaller portions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you pay close attention to what you eat and pay attention to your food intake, this could help you better appreciate the food, as your brain will have time to process what you put in your mouth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, it will reduce the amount of air bubbles you swallow with your meal which is the disastrous cause of bloating in the first place.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This way of eating is called "mindful eating".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This means that you should think about your food intake as a way to treat your body well and not overdo it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Basically, conscious consumption consists in not hurrying so that you can enjoy your food, cook your own meals, hydrate your body, do not multitask and above all, respect your body and your health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":490,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/elevated-view-hand-holding-turnips-soil-desk_23-2148181207.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-490"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kale and broccoli are indeed nutrient-dense and fiber-rich vegetables that you need to eat to have a strong digestive system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, these foods are also rich in raffinose, which is a sugar that can only be digested by bacteria in your stomach and its fermentation is exactly what makes you swell.&nbsp;Try to keep the amount you eat and maybe the steam or broths may reduce the amount of sugar you take.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":492,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535b.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-492"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you continue to be swollen, you may want to watch your salt intake.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eating foods high in sodium can slow body build up to get rid of excess water, which can make you feel like there''s a balloon in your stomach.&nbsp;You could digest a lot more sodium than ...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>your stomach.&nbsp;You could digest much more sodium than recommended by the American Heart Association, that is, no more than 1500 mg per day for adults.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Salt is extremely difficult to avoid due to its presence in most processed and prepackaged foods.&nbsp;If you feel like you''ve failed your healthy, almost salt-free diet, drink more water to flush it out of your body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":494,"width":426,"height":282,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535c.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-494" width="426" height="282"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you''ve been abusive with salty foods, you could invest in bananas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They prevent water from being trapped in your body due to sodium.&nbsp;Bananas are full of potassium and perfectly regulate salt levels to reduce bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meanwhile, the enzymes in papaya and pineapple also help break down proteins in your system, which wonderfully helps your stomach process food.&nbsp;So eat these fruits after a heavy meal to strengthen your digestive tract and help you avoid constipation and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a hearty meal, you may want to treat yourself to a cup of chamomile or peppermint tea.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":500,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535d.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-500"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both are known to relax spasms in your stomach and relieve your pain if you feel bloated.&nbsp;Chamomile tea not only helps digestion, but it can also relax and soothe you so you don''t pay as much attention to your belly problems.&nbsp;Peppermint oil is also available as a supplement if your cup of tea is not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotic yogurt puts you out of bloating with its active cultures.&nbsp;As you probably know, there are millions of different bacteria found in your stomach and some of them can cause excess gas in your digestive tract.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotics help regulate gas production and bloating if you are unlucky enough to suffer from it, and several studies have proven this.&nbsp;You can also take probiotic supplements instead of yogurt.&nbsp;If the yogurt is too sour for you, you can add honey or jam to sweeten this morning treat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":496,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535g.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-496"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you overeat and start to feel the annoying gas going up in your stomach, you can lie down and have someone do an abdominal massage for you, or you can do it yourself.&nbsp;This will help food move lower in your stomach and relieve tightness, excessive pressure and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":497,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535h.png" alt="" class="wp-image-497"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most people don''t like the idea of ​​moving around after a meal.&nbsp;But if you have freed yourself and are experiencing the first symptoms of gas and acid reflux, do not take medication immediately.&nbsp;Just fifteen minutes of yoga can be as useful as a pill and it''s much healthier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are several poses that can help relieve the tightness in your belly, helping your digestive tract to move food, stimulating your organs, and relieving the stress that partially causes bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":498,"width":417,"height":511,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535i.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-498" width="417" height="511"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whatever the time, you should never forget to hydrate your body. Water is actually a solution to many of the health problems you may be having, and one of them is bloating. Your daily consumption of water is supposed to be around 8 glasses and that doesn''t even count the other liquids you drink. So stay hydrated and your body will have all the power it needs to fight bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '10 Solid Ways To Reduce Stomach Bloating.', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', '10-solid-ways-to-reduce-stomach-bloating', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=474', 0, 'post', '', 0);
