p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most people don''t like the idea of ​​moving around after a meal.&nbsp;But if you have freed yourself and are experiencing the first symptoms of gas and acid reflux, do not take medication immediately.&nbsp;Just fifteen minutes of yoga can be as useful as a pill and it''s much healthier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are several poses that can help relieve the tightness in your belly, helping your digestive tract to move food, stimulating your organs, and relieving the stress that partially causes bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>AaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaAaaaaaaaaaaa</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whatever the time, you should never forget to hydrate your body. Water is actually a solution to many of the health problems you may be having, and one of them is bloating. Your daily consumption of water is supposed to be around 8 glasses and that doesn''t even count the other liquids you drink. So stay hydrated and your body will have all the power it needs to fight bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-22 10:22:31', '2020-02-22 10:22:31', '', 474, 'https://en.2fun.club/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2019-12-08 19:29:06', '2019-12-08 19:29:06', '<!-- wp:image {"id":868,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/people-2592247_1280-1024x678.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-868"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who has never felt back pain near the shoulder blades sometimes for no reason or as a result of harmless movement such as checking a blind spot or sneeze?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Anatomy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The thoracic region is complex because several structures are involved in this region. The rib cage is the region where the ribs form rings protecting our vital organs. The ribs on each side leave our sternum (in front) and come articulate with 2 corresponding vertebrae in the back. We have a total of 12 ribs, 2 of which are floating (which do not join the sternum).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>biomechanics</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The ribs are mainly a rolling movement on the vertebra during breathing (inspiration / expiration) and also, during back movements (rotations, lean). In addition, a multitude of nerve circuits and several muscle layers overlap in this section of the body. It can therefore be simple to get hurt and have a referenced origin that may explain a pain in the back.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>origin</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>  Sternum</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An impact to the sternum can affect the mobility of the rib with its corresponding vertebra in the back, because with the ring-shaped anatomy, this creates a restriction of movement at arm''s length distance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>  Cough / sneeze</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Repeated coughing or intense sneezing increases abdominal pressure, causing chest expansion. This can then cause a rib / vertebra joint blockage. It can also result in an increase in the tension of the respiratory muscles, including the intercostals that are between each side.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>  Posture and other injuries with compensation</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Poor posture usually involving the neck will result in a more rounded posture of the back with some rigidity. In addition, a fragility in the lumbar could then compensate for a higher stiffness in dorsal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A shoulder injury will change the mobility and control of the scapula as it slides over the rib cage. It "holds" in space mainly by the complex musculature connecting it to the shoulder and the thoracic spine. Thus, the alteration of the movement of the shoulder will result in an indirect change by muscle and joint compensation of the column and corresponding ribs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Physiotherapy</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Physiotherapy treatments are very effective in this type of problem. A detailed and specific evaluation allows us to clearly identify the probable sources. We then have the ability to restore the movement of the ribs and spine, reduce muscle tension, identify an external source (eg the shoulder) and correct it. We will also provide postural guidance and rib cage strengthening and mobility exercises, including scapular strengthening exercises.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Exercises to avoid chest pain', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'exercises-to-avoid-chest-pain', '', '', '2020-04-23 12:05:39', '2020-04-23 12:05:39', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=214', 0, 'post', '', 0),
