(670, 1, '2020-03-14 22:44:11', '2020-03-14 22:44:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A desire to chew ice or to eat something salty all the time can be a sign of a deeper problem or a lack of minerals and vitamins, specialists say. That’s why it’s always a good idea to pay attention to any new developing habits, especially if they arise suddenly from out of nowhere.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We at Bright Side have made a list of things your body may try to tell you in hopes to help you live a long and happy life!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. A&nbsp;crawling, creeping feeling in&nbsp;your legs</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":662,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230734-image-crop-1498x1050-1582210105-728-32e9147584-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-662"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If&nbsp;you have weird sensations in&nbsp;your legs and feet like crawling, creeping, or&nbsp;the urge to&nbsp;move, it&nbsp;may be&nbsp;a&nbsp;symptom of&nbsp;restless leg syndrome. This disorder is&nbsp;long-term and you often feel this discomfort at&nbsp;night when you’re trying to&nbsp;get some rest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. Thickening of&nbsp;the skin</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":642,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230735-image-crop-4596x4000-1582207715-728-4795cc3acc-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-642"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don’t ignore skin problems or&nbsp;underestimate them. When the skin&nbsp;becomes thick&nbsp;and itchy, it&nbsp;can be&nbsp;a&nbsp;sign of&nbsp;a&nbsp;bunch of&nbsp;internal problems&nbsp;like a&nbsp;hormonal disorder, eczema, or&nbsp;allergies. You can have some blood tests done if&nbsp;this problem persists or&nbsp;if&nbsp;it&nbsp;appears to&nbsp;be&nbsp;getting worse.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3. A&nbsp;change in&nbsp;handwriting, a&nbsp;loss of&nbsp;smell, and intense dreams</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":643,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230716-shutterstock_742328920-1582208556-728-9829a42259-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-643"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Everyone has likely heard of&nbsp;Parkinson’s disease&nbsp;but not as&nbsp;many of&nbsp;us know its symptoms. Tremors, slowness of&nbsp;movement, poor sleep along with nightmares, and speech and writing changes can be&nbsp;signs of&nbsp;the disease, doctors warn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. Anger and aggressive behavior</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":644,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230736-image-crop-1350x1332-1582207540-728-42cca98274-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-644"/><figcaption>© Frank Hoermann/SVEN SIMON</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bursts of&nbsp;anger may not always be&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;your personality. In&nbsp;fact, it&nbsp;could be&nbsp;connected to&nbsp;depression,&nbsp;some researchers say. According to&nbsp;them, depression isn’t always just about having a&nbsp;lack of&nbsp;energy or&nbsp;experiencing sadness&nbsp;— you can have aggressive behavior as&nbsp;well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. Sleeping too much</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":646,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230721-shutterstock_1015910641-1582208621-728-4ac31df3ec-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-646"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This disorder is&nbsp;called&nbsp;hypersomnia&nbsp;and it&nbsp;may stem from things that prove it&nbsp;isn’t just tiredness, doctors say. Some autoimmune diseases may cause the feeling of&nbsp;wanting to&nbsp;fall asleep just about anywhere. Also, having&nbsp;alcoholic&nbsp;beverages before sleeping may cause this effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<center><figure class="wp-block-image"><a href="https://skoura24.com/50-dangerous-household-items/2"><img src="https://youintouch.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Read-More-icon-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-320"/></a></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6. Changes in&nbsp;eye color</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":647,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230720-62534160-d65c7e88c21b3967e9dd04700adaa44085c3e0a4-1500-1-1582204735-728-752af887f2-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-647"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If&nbsp;there’s a&nbsp;white or&nbsp;grey ring&nbsp;around the cornea of&nbsp;the eyes, it&nbsp;may be&nbsp;a&nbsp;sign of&nbsp;high cholesterol for people under 45&nbsp;years old, doctors have noticed. The ring is&nbsp;harmless by&nbsp;itself and has only a&nbsp;visual effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7. Salt cravings</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":648,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230719-shutterstock_358578326-1582208653-728-b54324f6ad-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-648"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s okay to&nbsp;like salty food but when you can’t control it&nbsp;anymore and&nbsp;salty&nbsp;foodbecomes the only thing you want, it’s time to&nbsp;ask yourself why. This can signify an&nbsp;iron deficiency, anemia, dehydration or&nbsp;premenstrual syndrome, according to&nbsp;medical sources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8. Forgetfulness, fatigue, and a&nbsp;low libido</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":650,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230718-shutterstock_767546119-1582207842-728-7ce4a4d49e-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-650"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sometimes people confuse this with depression because it&nbsp;looks like you’re so&nbsp;tired and fed up&nbsp;with everything that you don’t have the energy to&nbsp;remember things. Doctors share that it’s better not to&nbsp;ignore such a&nbsp;condition because it&nbsp;can signify a&nbsp;thyroid hormone&nbsp;issue in&nbsp;the body. You also may gain weight and feel cold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9. Always feeling thirsty</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":649,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230717-shutterstock_1587320314-1582207891-728-570b9084e7-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-649"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s not normal to&nbsp;feel thirsty&nbsp;all the time, specialists say. There are some cases when it&nbsp;can be&nbsp;connected to&nbsp;the food that you eat, so&nbsp;check to&nbsp;see if&nbsp;you’re eating too many spicy or&nbsp;salty products. The incessant thirst could also be&nbsp;a&nbsp;sign of&nbsp;diabetes or&nbsp;pregnancy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10. Wanting to&nbsp;chew ice</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":651,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230715-shutterstock_1564081801-1582207762-728-07c393e7df-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-651"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A&nbsp;wish to&nbsp;crunch ice can be&nbsp;easily explained and it&nbsp;may be&nbsp;more than just a&nbsp;habit. An&nbsp;iron deficiency or&nbsp;anemia&nbsp;could be&nbsp;the reason for this unusual desire, some&nbsp;research&nbsp;has shown. You may want to&nbsp;have some blood tests taken to&nbsp;check and see if&nbsp;you need to&nbsp;start taking supplements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What other surprising symptoms do&nbsp;you know of&nbsp;that could reveal things about your body’s condition? Please share your stories in&nbsp;the comments as&nbsp;they could be&nbsp;useful for someone else!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '10 Ways Your Body May Be Telling You Something’s Wrong', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '628-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-14 22:44:11', '2020-03-14 22:44:11', '', 628, 'https://en.2fun.club/628-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(667, 1, '2020-03-14 22:32:37', '2020-03-14 22:32:37', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A desire to chew ice or to eat something salty all the time can be a sign of a deeper problem or a lack of minerals and vitamins, specialists say. That’s why it’s always a good idea to pay attention to any new developing habits, especially if they arise suddenly from out of nowhere.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We at Bright Side have made a list of things your body may try to tell you in hopes to help you live a long and happy life!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. A&nbsp;crawling, creeping feeling in&nbsp;your legs</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":662,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230734-image-crop-1498x1050-1582210105-728-32e9147584-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-662"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If&nbsp;you have weird sensations in&nbsp;your legs and feet like crawling, creeping, or&nbsp;the urge to&nbsp;move, it&nbsp;may be&nbsp;a&nbsp;symptom of&nbsp;restless leg syndrome. This disorder is&nbsp;long-term and you often feel this discomfort at&nbsp;night when you’re trying to&nbsp;get some rest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. Thickening of&nbsp;the skin</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":642,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230735-image-crop-4596x4000-1582207715-728-4795cc3acc-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-642"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Don’t ignore skin problems or&nbsp;underestimate them. When the skin&nbsp;becomes thick&nbsp;and itchy, it&nbsp;can be&nbsp;a&nbsp;sign of&nbsp;a&nbsp;bunch of&nbsp;internal problems&nbsp;like a&nbsp;hormonal disorder, eczema, or&nbsp;allergies. You can have some blood tests done if&nbsp;this problem persists or&nbsp;if&nbsp;it&nbsp;appears to&nbsp;be&nbsp;getting worse.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3. A&nbsp;change in&nbsp;handwriting, a&nbsp;loss of&nbsp;smell, and intense dreams</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":643,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230716-shutterstock_742328920-1582208556-728-9829a42259-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-643"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Everyone has likely heard of&nbsp;Parkinson’s disease&nbsp;but not as&nbsp;many of&nbsp;us know its symptoms. Tremors, slowness of&nbsp;movement, poor sleep along with nightmares, and speech and writing changes can be&nbsp;signs of&nbsp;the disease, doctors warn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. Anger and aggressive behavior</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":644,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230736-image-crop-1350x1332-1582207540-728-42cca98274-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-644"/><figcaption>© Frank Hoermann/SVEN SIMON</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bursts of&nbsp;anger may not always be&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;your personality. In&nbsp;fact, it&nbsp;could be&nbsp;connected to&nbsp;depression,&nbsp;some researchers say. According to&nbsp;them, depression isn’t always just about having a&nbsp;lack of&nbsp;energy or&nbsp;experiencing sadness&nbsp;— you can have aggressive behavior as&nbsp;well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. Sleeping too much</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":646,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230721-shutterstock_1015910641-1582208621-728-4ac31df3ec-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-646"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This disorder is&nbsp;called&nbsp;hypersomnia&nbsp;and it&nbsp;may stem from things that prove it&nbsp;isn’t just tiredness, doctors say. Some autoimmune diseases may cause the feeling of&nbsp;wanting to&nbsp;fall asleep just about anywhere. Also, having&nbsp;alcoholic&nbsp;beverages before sleeping may cause this effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<center><div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter is-resized"><a href="https://getfits.club/15-signs-that-your-kidneys-arent-working-properly/2"><img src="https://inquizs.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Capture-removebg-preview.png" alt="" class="wp-image-1120" width="320" height="50"/></a></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6. Changes in&nbsp;eye color</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":647,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/15230720-62534160-d65c7e88c21b3967e9dd04700adaa44085c3e0a4-1500-1-1582204735-728-752af887f2-1582703428.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-647"/><figcaption>© shutterstock.com</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If&nbsp;there’s a&nbsp;white or&nbsp;grey ring&nbsp;around the cornea of&nbsp;the eyes, it&nbsp;may be&nbsp;a&nbsp;sign of&nbsp;high cholesterol for people under 45&nbsp;years old, doctors have noticed. The ring is&nbsp;harmless by&nbsp;itself and has only a&nbsp;visual effect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph 