(381, 1, '2020-01-01 22:00:04', '2020-01-01 22:00:04', '<!-- wp:image {"id":384,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/1577919461088.png" alt="" class="wp-image-384"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ah! The stress! This unloved one we would like to get rid of forever. The message is hammered over and over, being stressed is bad. Do you, too, get stressed out … about being stressed?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Chase away bad stress</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Be aware that stress is not always negative! It is a normal reaction, almost like a survival reflex of our organism when it is confronted with a given situation. It is he who allows you to take your legs to your neck if, for example, you are chased by a three-headed monster. Joking aside, stress is not only essential to react quickly in the event of danger, but it is also an ally if it is well managed. The danger, precisely, is when your body sees all situations as an enemy to fight. So there, nothing is going right! Chronic stress, the nasty bad type of stress, hits you. High pressure, increased heart rate, muscle tension, disturbed sleep and more. At this point, you have to find solutions to de-stress before stress steals your health. In a nutshell, here are some ideas (some rather unusual) to tame stress!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>A small infusion</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Drinking a good herbal tea would help reduce stress. Lavender, for example, has soothing properties. Before going to bed, lemon balm or even delicious verbena, two plants that are easy to grow in your garden, promote relaxation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Essential oils</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depending on the essential oil chosen, aromatherapy has powerful soothing effects. Why not combine these benefits with those of a good long hot bath after a long day at work? All it takes is a few drops of the lavender bath and massage oil and presto, take the opportunity to take down. The ultimate relaxation!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Music… not just classical</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Of course, classical music is an excellent way to de-stress. It is even responsible, according to studies, for lowering the level of stress hormones. Don''t roll your eyes too quickly if Mozart is not your cup of tea! Any kind of music, as long as you like, will have surprising beneficial effects on your body by lowering your heart rate and blood pressure, which increase when stressed!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Meditation, yoga and breathing</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether it''s from an online tutorial, signing up for a class in your neighborhood, or from a mobile app, meditation and yoga are accessible and help relieve stress and focus on the present moment. Nothing better to refocus on yourself and the positive that surrounds you. Both activities are also good for learning a few breathing techniques that will calm you down in times of great stress. Ressssspirez.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Laugh at… de-stress</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You don''t even have to spend to see your favorite comedian or take out your old joke book. You will find everything you need on the Internet to have a good laugh (and sometimes to tears) every day. Whether watching hilarious clips of cats or those reminding us of the good old years of "funny video", laughter increases the production of endorphins and leads to a great state of relaxation and relaxation. Did you know that children laugh more than 300 times a day while adults barely do it 10 times? The time has come to find your child''s heart again, don''t you think?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Your ancestors held the anti-stress secret</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manual work because of the repetitive movements it involves has an almost immediate soothing effect. Knitting, in particular, would be as effective as meditation. No need for another woolen sweater? Try sewing, woodworking, pottery, weaving or why not, gardening! For a more contemporary hobby, nothing better than coloring. Dust your old felt-tip pens and go look for a coloring book in a bookstore. Thanks to its popularity in recent years there is something for everyone!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You see, there are many effective strategies to keep bad stress away from your life. Spending time in nature, being active, going out with friends, getting lost in a good book, and even cooking are also simple ways to reduce it. It is still necessary to find the right formula and avoid that your anti-stress activities … become stressful. In other words, if meditating calms you down, but the journey between the mediation course and the house is a nightmare of traffic jams and detours … let''s say that the formula is not winning! Knitting, maybe?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ideas to relax, naturally de-stress', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'ideas-to-relax-naturally-de-stress', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=381', 0, 'post', '', 0),
