(414, 1, '2020-01-20 15:17:04', '2020-01-20 15:17:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the majority of cases, the manifestations of allergy are limited to the site of aggression of the allergen (nose, eyes, lungs, skin) and do not put life in danger. But sometimes, they may require care.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In allergy, the range of symptoms is wide and often confusing because all organs are likely to be concerned. Allergens can enter the body in three ways: cutaneous, respiratory or digestive. The reactions are mostly local. If they are generalized, rapid support is needed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The local reactions, very variable, are manifested with an intensity that changes a lot from one person to another. They can even change over time, in the sense of improvement, or on the contrary, an aggravation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Runny nose</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A few grains of pollen in suspension are enough to trigger, in predisposed people, bursts of sneezing as irrepressible as explosive. In severe cases, these bursts follow one another 10 to 30 times in succession and are repeated in crises. This is to say if one can feel a state of fatigue and exhaustion at the end of these mini-earthquakes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Often morning sneeze is associated with itching in the area of ​​the nose and throat and a runny nose. It is truly an avalanche of clear liquid, similar to water, which can not be mistaken for a viral cold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The stuffy and/or itchy nose is also characteristic of an allergic cold. Nasal obstruction, sometimes of both nostrils, is due to swelling of the mucosa and secretions. The permanent impression of nasal congestion can be painful, especially at night.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The eyes that cry</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hay fever is very often accompanied by inflammation of the eyes. It is conjunctivitis of allergic origin. The eyes are irritated, giving the impression of having sand under the eyelids. And that’s not all. The intense tingling and the burning sensation are the source of unbearable itching, followed by active scratching sessions. Suddenly, the eyelids begin to swell and the whiteness of the eye turns red. To crown this feverish gaze, the eyes constantly appear on the brink of tears and can no longer stand the light.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At more chronic exposures to allergens (animal hair, dust mites, molds), the symptoms are less intense, but not less painful: tearing, red eyes and eyelids stuck in the morning, eyelashes torn off from rub the eyes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Itchy mouth or skin</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The skin and pulp of certain fruits or vegetables (apple, pear, cherry, peach, tomatoes, carrots …), as well as some spices (paprika, curry …), can, as soon as they are ingested, cause itching of the mouth and the throat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eczematous skin, on the other hand, itches terribly. To the touch, the surface of the lesions caused by eczema is reminiscent of granite. Vesicles – tiny blisters filled with a clear liquid – are formed and the liquid released when scratching then flows over the surface of the lesion, then dries forming small crusts. Note that recent eczema lesions are often preceded by itching. After the acute stage, the redness fades, the skin clears, becomes drier and peels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Of a different appearance, chronic eczema retains old lesions contributing to the thickening of the skin. It consists of red cupboards that peel continuously. Sometimes, abrasions or scratches due to scraping appear. Finally, the lesions located on the palms of the hands and the soles of the feet can be cracked, cracked. These cracks then cause discomfort and significant pain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In children, especially toddlers, the appearance of eczema varies. Red patches may be covered with small vesicles or scabs, or they may be dry or oozing. In all cases, itching, except probably in infants under six months. In infants, eczematous lesions sit mainly on the face: cheeks, forehead, and chin. After the age of two, and sometimes before, they tend to migrate to the elbows, behind the knees, the instep, the neck and sometimes around the mouth and on the hands. As with adults, intensive scraping thickens the skin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Blistered skin</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The symptoms of urticaria are not deceiving: eruptions in relief, identical to those caused by nettle. At the origin of these superficial lesions, there is a slight swelling of the skin. In some cases, the urticaria is accompanied by a deeper swelling, called angioedema. Urticaria is characterized by tiny pink-colored pimples with a white center, called papules. They are fleeting in nature and “travel”: they appear and then disappear on the skin just as quickly. They are accompanied by intense, even unbearable itching. The papules may be tiny or, on the contrary, be closets, not without mentioning a map. In some cases, the urticaria can escalate into a more severe reaction.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Tormented digestion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just arrived in the stomach, some foods can hurt us: burns, nausea, and vomiting. Uncommon symptoms may also indicate indigestion, intolerance or food poisoning. Hence the interest of consulting a specialist to make the difference and make a precise diagnosis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wheezing</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The allergen transported by the air, such as pollen or cat’s hair, is able to penetrate very far into the body. When it comes into contact with the bronchi of a predisposed person, they will close, like a spring, against the intruder: it is the bronchial spasm or asthma. As a result of this obstruction, the air tends to get stuck inside. Hence the need to force to expel the air. This respiratory discomfort causes shortness of breath and may result in whistling, which is produced by the passage of air through the narrowed bronchi. However, it should also be known that the first symptom of asthma, before whistling, is sometimes a dry cough.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Respiratory alert signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Signs of a severe crisis requiring emergency treatment? The person can not lie down and has the sensation of choking; his breathing becomes harder and harder, causing sweating, faster heart rate, and anxiety. Showing the drop in the amount of oxygen in the blood, fingers, and lips can cyanose and take a blue-violet color. Asthma can also result in permanent shortness of breath, on which crises can be added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Allergic reactions: recognize localized manifestations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '413-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-01-20 15:17:04', '2020-01-20 15:17:04', '', 413, 'https://en.2fun.club/413-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
