(417, 1, '2020-01-22 21:18:24', '2020-01-22 21:18:24', '<!-- wp:image {"id":421,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/people-3149372_1280-1-819x1024.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-421"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bodybuilding exercises can be very varied.&nbsp;Long series or short series, intensity of the contraction, number of series on the same muscle group, rest time, concentric, eccentric, static or plyometric contraction, pre-fatigue, body weight or overload… All these parameters can be modulated for aim for different muscle goals.&nbsp;What are the basic principles for building muscle mass?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>What is going on in the muscle?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The volume of a muscle depends on 2 main elements: the type and size of the&nbsp;number of&nbsp;muscle&nbsp;fibers&nbsp;, the quantity of&nbsp;fat cells&nbsp;(adipocytes) present.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Generally, bodybuilding stimulates the multiplication of muscle fibers.&nbsp;On the other hand, this process is accompanied or not by an increase in the local reserves of fats.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We therefore speak of&nbsp;dry mass&nbsp;gain&nbsp;or&nbsp;fat mass gain&nbsp;.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3 major elements will condition the morphology of your muscles, namely:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1 / The type of exercises practiced during bodybuilding sessions</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2 / The amount of “pure” cardio sport practiced per week</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3 / Food</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your objective is to develop your muscle mass by limiting the stocks of fat cells, you will have to play on these 3 parameters:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&gt; The&nbsp;exercises will be targeted&nbsp;and precise during the weight training sessions.&nbsp;At least 3 hours per week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&gt; Regular&nbsp;cardio sport&nbsp;(swimming, running, cycling, elliptical cross trainer, etc.) is necessary.&nbsp;At least 3 hours per week.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&gt; A&nbsp;diet&nbsp;rich in vegetables, fruits, dried fruits and proteins (white meat).&nbsp;Poor in industrial sugars (cakes, sweets ...), fats (cold meats, fatty meats ...).&nbsp;No excess food.&nbsp;Eat healthy in reasonable quantities&nbsp;&nbsp;!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>What bodybuilding exercises?</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During weight training, the precision of the exercises will optimize the effectiveness of your workouts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Series&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prefer rather short series (about 10 movements).&nbsp;This means that you must feel a frank difficulty on the last 3-4 movements of each series.&nbsp;To do this, adjust the intensity of the muscle contraction (weight, muscle pre-fatigue, variation in rest times, etc.)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Muscle stroke</strong>:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Efficiency will be optimum in medium running (intermediate position between elongated muscle and shortened muscle position).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4>Type of contraction&nbsp;&nbsp;:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We recommend varying the type of contraction.&nbsp;Even if, it is true, concentric dynamic contraction (towards the shortening of the muscle) is the most recommended to develop the number of muscle fibers, it will be preferable to also practice plyometric exercises (pumps, squats etc) and isometric (static cladding, chair against the wall etc).&nbsp;Indeed, our muscles are conditioned to be versatile!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Contraction speed</strong>&nbsp;:</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Do not hesitate to vary the speed of movement.&nbsp;Slow speed is recommended, but fast speed exercises will allow you to gain explosiveness.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Body weight or overload?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The load (weight, weighted vests, etc.) must be adapted to your abilities.&nbsp;If you are able to lift the bench press only 3 times you may need to remove weight.&nbsp;Indeed, we said earlier that it was recommended to aim for series of 10 movements.&nbsp;The load must be adjusted accordingly.&nbsp;Over the series, the muscle will inevitably tire.&nbsp;Then reduce the additional load.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bodyweight exercises are quite effective contrary to what we sometimes hear.&nbsp;To increase the difficulty, decrease the pause time between each series and use pre-fatigue!&nbsp;For example, in the pump position, go down on the arms and do not move for 10 seconds then continue directly with a series of 10 movements at slow speed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Number of sessions / week:</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3 to 4 one hour sessions per week recommended.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->\n<h4><strong>Which muscles?&nbsp;</strong></h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prefer exercises in muscle chains.&nbsp;Why ?&nbsp;A series of squats on one leg is more natural for the body than analytical hamstring strength training on a machine.&nbsp;This also helps to avoid muscle imbalances.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Precautions</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bodybuilding places great demands on joints and tendons.&nbsp;An injury will stop you for many months.&nbsp;This is why we recommend respecting a very important principle: the principle of&nbsp;progressiveness&nbsp;&nbsp;!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Indeed, many athletes do not respect this very simple principle.&nbsp;We then deplore a large number of injuries, especially among beginners.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ask yourself the right questions.&nbsp;When was my last training: a few days, a few months, several years, never?&nbsp;Is my body used to being subjected to so many stresses all at once?&nbsp;Are some joints already fragile?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Listen to your body because small pains sometimes become big pains!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Building muscle mass: basic principles', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'building-muscle-mass-basic-principles', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=417', 0, 'post', '', 2),
