(426, 1, '2020-01-25 00:27:37', '2020-01-25 00:27:37', '<!-- wp:image {"id":431,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/weights-652486_1280-1024x684.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-431"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The question comes up often. Is registration in a gym necessary? In fact, many bodybuilding exercises can be practiced at home with very little equipment. What then are the real benefits of a gym? Are we progressing faster in the gym and why? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Equipment</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In weight rooms, there are many machines that both target different muscle groups but also adapt resistance to contraction . In our article devoted to training plans in muscle development Gaining muscle mass: basic principles we explain that the workload of muscle is paramount in this type of training. You will indeed have to perform series of ten movements which corresponds to a load of the order of 75 to 80% of the maximum muscle resistance (RM).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depending on the muscle groups targeted, this is not always easy! Take the example of squat type reinforcement. If you do a series of 10 descents supported on both legs and without additional load, the muscular effort will probably not be intense enough to develop muscle volume effectively. But there are always tips: use the static or dynamic prefatigue ! What is that ?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Descend relatively low and stay in position without moving for 10 seconds. Always keep the other leg in the air and directly follow a series of 10 ascents-descents at slow speed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What happened ? You have exhausted the resources of the muscle by a prefatigue before requesting it on a series of 10 movements. It is a completely relevant alternative to the press machine that is usually found in a weight room.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On this same exercise, you can bring a different variant: still resting on one leg, descend relatively low and perform small knee flexion movements, with little amplitude while maintaining significant knee flexion. Continue like this for 10 seconds then continue with a "classic" series of larger flexing movements at slower speed. This is called dynamic prefatigue .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For each muscle group, adjustments are possible. You just need a little imagination! If you want to strengthen yourself effectively at home, a minimum of equipment still seems essential: weights, TRX type exercise strap, pull-up bar. Remember, there are many things you can do at “bodyweight”. Machines are not always compulsory to obtain interesting results!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>coaching</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the big interests of the weight rooms is the coaches. They will give you advice on how to avoid injuries , how to use the machines correctly. They will be able to guide you on specific training plans .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unfortunately, in reality, they are often understaffed in theaters. Do not choose your room solely according to the price but also according to the staff.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The coaches bring their knowledge and experience , but also motivation, an essential element to continue and progress in the long term!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Motivation</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get real results, it takes time. At the risk of disappointing you, forget the miracle cures, the physical transformations in 6 weeks! You will have to change your lifestyle, but not only for a month! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Motivation is therefore essential and must be sustainable. Many believe that registering in a gym will “force” us to go to make the subscription profitable. Is this argument valid? Some sports halls show alarming statistics: between 50 and 80% of new registrants in January no longer come in March… On average, new registrants come to the gym 4 times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The practice of Crossfit has been booming in recent years. It offers group sessions with new challenges to be taken up constantly. The principle of group emulation seems to work more. It is therefore an interesting alternative to “classic” weight training rooms from the point of view of motivation. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In summary, registering in a gym is not at all an obligation to progress in bodybuilding. Reinforcement will be effective without or with very little equipment, provided that adaptations are found. Achieving your goals depends mainly on you and your motivation  ! So at work, don''t give up, don''t give up! </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Bodybuilding: inside or outside the home?', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'bodybuilding-inside-or-outside-the-home', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=426', 0, 'post', '', 0),
