(585, 1, '2020-03-05 21:22:27', '2020-03-05 21:22:27', '<!-- wp:image {"id":588,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1583446758375.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-588"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->\n<p class="has-medium-font-size">Not only animal products contain protein.&nbsp;There are numerous plant sources that contain even more protein than meat, dairy or eggs.&nbsp;Here are some examples:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>Spirulina</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It contains about 60 - 70% complete proteins, which means it has all the 8 essential amino acids and 10 non-essential acids needed for iron health.&nbsp;It also contains protein, in an amount greater than beef, chicken or soy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Its nutrients are superior to any other source, and then specialists talk about gamma-linoleic acid (GLA), vitamin B12, iron, and many other components that have been established to protect against cancer.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another quality of this small plant is that once it reaches the stomach, it is very easy to digest.&nbsp;It lowers cholesterol, protects the immune system, stimulates the absorption of minerals.&nbsp;A true source of life, spirulina energizes and protects against influenza and colds, herpes, speeds up healing in diseases such as measles, mumps.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>spinach</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Popeye''s secret is for nothing spinach.&nbsp;A single cup of cooked spinach has over 5 grams of protein and is also a very good source of calcium, iron and vitamin C.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>Hemp seeds</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hemp seeds contain 6 g of protein / 100 g. Researchers have found that hemp seeds are the only source of edible protein completely assimilated by the human body.&nbsp;So in the salads you prepare add a handful of such seeds, preferably ground to be better absorbed proteins.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>broccoli</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It contains more protein than beef.&nbsp;In addition, it has amino acids, fiber, and vitamin B6.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>almonds</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They are full of protein and healthy fats, good for the heart. They are also rich in minerals, including manganese, which helps to strengthen bones and regulate blood sugar, and magnesium, essential for the functioning of organs, muscles and nerves, for controlling blood glucose and regulating blood pressure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Five vegetables higher in protein than meat', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'five-vegetables-higher-in-protein-than-meat', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=585', 0, 'post', '', 0),
