e sodium than ...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>your stomach.&nbsp;You could digest much more sodium than recommended by the American Heart Association, that is, no more than 1500 mg per day for adults.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Salt is extremely difficult to avoid due to its presence in most processed and prepackaged foods.&nbsp;If you feel like you''ve failed your healthy, almost salt-free diet, drink more water to flush it out of your body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":494,"width":426,"height":282,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535c.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-494" width="426" height="282"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you''ve been abusive with salty foods, you could invest in bananas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They prevent water from being trapped in your body due to sodium.&nbsp;Bananas are full of potassium and perfectly regulate salt levels to reduce bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meanwhile, the enzymes in papaya and pineapple also help break down proteins in your system, which wonderfully helps your stomach process food.&nbsp;So eat these fruits after a heavy meal to strengthen your digestive tract and help you avoid constipation and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a hearty meal, you may want to treat yourself to a cup of chamomile or peppermint tea.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":500,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535d.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-500"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both are known to relax spasms in your stomach and relieve your pain if you feel bloated.&nbsp;Chamomile tea not only helps digestion, but it can also relax and soothe you so you don''t pay as much attention to your belly problems.&nbsp;Peppermint oil is also available as a supplement if your cup of tea is not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotic yogurt puts you out of bloating with its active cultures.&nbsp;As you probably know, there are millions of different bacteria found in your stomach and some of them can cause excess gas in your digestive tract.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotics help regulate gas production and bloating if you are unlucky enough to suffer from it, and several studies have proven this.&nbsp;You can also take probiotic supplements instead of yogurt.&nbsp;If the yogurt is too sour for you, you can add honey or jam to sweeten this morning treat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":496,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535g.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-496"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you overeat and start to feel the annoying gas going up in your stomach, you can lie down and have someone do an abdominal massage for you, or you can do it yourself.&nbsp;This will help food move lower in your stomach and relieve tightness, excessive pressure and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":497,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535h.png" alt="" class="wp-image-497"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most people don''t like the idea of ​​moving around after a meal.&nbsp;But if you have freed yourself and are experiencing the first symptoms of gas and acid reflux, do not take medication immediately.&nbsp;Just fifteen minutes of yoga can be as useful as a pill and it''s much healthier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are several poses that can help relieve the tightness in your belly, helping your digestive tract to move food, stimulating your organs, and relieving the stress that partially causes bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":498,"width":417,"height":511,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535i.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-498" width="417" height="511"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whatever the time, you should never forget to hydrate your body.&nbsp;Water is actually a solution to many of the health problems you may be having, and one of them is bloating.&nbsp;Your daily consumption of water is supposed to be around 8 glasses and that doesn''t even count the other liquids you drink.&nbsp;So stay hydrated and your body will have all the power it needs to fight bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '10 Solid Ways To Reduce Stomach Bloating.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-22 23:14:50', '2020-02-22 23:14:50', '', 474, 'https://en.2fun.club/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(510, 1, '2020-02-22 23:19:29', '2020-02-22 23:19:29', '<!-- wp:image {"id":373,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/scientific-medical-infographic-atherosclerosis_1308-32788.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-373"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  The leading cause of death in the world, according to the World Health Organization (WHO), cardiovascular disease is a group of disorders affecting the heart and blood vessels. Several factors lead to the appearance of these, such as smoking, physical inactivity, diabetes or even hyperlipidemia. To guard against cardiovascular disease, it is essential to adopt a healthy lifestyle and to favor foods that improve the health of the arteries. Here are 15 foods to include in your diet to protect against cardiovascular disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  Heart attacks, strokes, atherosclerosis, all of which can be life-threatening. The E-Times tells us that to avoid them, it is essential to have a healthy lifestyle by promoting exercise and foods that clean the arteries. Did you know that sardines are good for cardiovascular health? If you read the following lines, you will know what you need to incorporate into your diet to protect your arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1- Orange</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":444,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/sliced-whole-oranges_144627-3981.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-444"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Citrus is the ideal food for clearing arteries. It is full of pectins and thus blocks the absorption of bad cholesterol by the body. According to this study, frequent consumption of orange juice allows a considerable drop in the cholesterol present in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>2- kale</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":446,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/meal-vegetable-food-agriculture-vitamin_1203-5924.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-446"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Leafy vegetables are recommended for cleaning the arteries, especially kale. Rich in omega 3, antioxidants and fiber, this food should be preferred by people likely to develop arterial disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3- Spinach</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":448,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/top-view-bowl-salad-cloth_23-2148381242.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-448"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in vitamin A and C, spinach is also a great source of beta carotene. According to this study, this food is very effective in combating the stiffness of the arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4- pomegranate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":450,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/exotic-delicious-pomegranate-white-background_144627-12572.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-450"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This delicious fruit is effective in clearing the arteries. Rich in punic acid and antioxidants, it prevents plaque from forming inside the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: its consumption helps fight against all cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5- Sesame seeds</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":452,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/various-seeds-sesame-flax-seed-flax-seeds-pumpkin-seed-poppy-chia-bowls-rustic-copy_114579-3953.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-452"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> These seeds are ideal for combating the development of atherosclerosis. According to this study, their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory power acts as a real shield for the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6- Garlic</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":454,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unpeeled-garlic_144627-12048.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-454"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Renowned for many virtues, garlic is also effective in reducing plaque and blood pressure. According to the researchers, the food is useful in reducing the effects of atherosclerosis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7- Dark chocolate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":456,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/chocolate-dark-coffee-confiserie-65882.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-456"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its richness in cocoa and flavonoids, dark chocolate helps make the arteries more flexible and thus prevent heart disease. A small square per day is advisable to enjoy its benefits on overall health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8- Lemon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":458,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/lemon_1205-1668.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-458"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its powerful antioxidant power, lemon is excellent for the health of the arteries and the heart. The citrus fruit is also rich in vitamin C, helping to reduce inflammation and lower the cholesterol level in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9- Turmeric</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":460,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/turmeric-powder_1323-400.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-460"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The golden spice is effective in fighting atherosclerosis and lowering cholesterol levels in the blood. Rich in polyphenols, it helps protect the arteries and more generally the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10- Sardines</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":462,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-3650159.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-462"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in omega 3 and fatty acids, sardines are the most recommended fish for heart health. They increase levels of good cholesterol as well as reduce inflammation. According to this study, sardines help protect cardiovascular health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>11- Lentils</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":464,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pardina-lentils_1368-8865.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-464"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their richness in magnesium, potassium and proteins, lentils help to reduce the plaque present in the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: the consumption of these oilseeds is recommended for the heart.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>12- Almond</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":467,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/almonds_1339-237.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-467"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their antioxidant power, almonds are recommended for coronary health. According to the researchers, they lower the hyperlipidemia responsible for most cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>13- Watermelon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":469,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-1398655.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-469"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in citrulline, an amino acid, watermelon helps to heal inflammation and cleanse the arteries. This fruit is also rich in nitric oxide, an element that reduces blood pressure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>14- Blueberries</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":471,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/ripe-blueberry-green-leaves-cup_23-2148196308.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-471"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Blueberries are prized for their antioxidant action. They reduce the plaque responsible for atherosclerosis and fight against free radicals responsible for cardiovascular disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Caution :</strong><br> Before introducing these foods into your diet, it is essential to consult a specialist doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '14 foods you should eat to clean your arteries and keep them healthy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-22 23:19:29', '2020-02-22 23:19:29', '', 312, 'https://en.2fun.club/312-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
