Regular rotation of fresh orange juice helps to meet the needs of daily calcium . It works to cleanse the mouth by eliminating harmful bacteria . After drinking the juice you need to brush the teeth because it is acidic .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>10 – apples:</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prevents leakage and maintain the health of the teeth . You need to eat apples regularly , as it helps to increase the secretion of saliva in the mouth and prevents the accumulation of food residue . Plus, it has many minerals and vitamins specialized .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They also help to clean the teeth, so you need to take it after meals , and also the process of chewing gum is a type of exercise for dental jaw . You can get chewing gum of sugar in different flavors so depending on what you prefer . </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'best foods for dental health', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '439-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-23 00:51:52', '2020-02-23 00:51:52', '', 439, 'https://en.2fun.club/439-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(518, 1, '2020-02-23 15:39:18', '2020-02-23 15:39:18', '<!-- wp:image {"id":486,"width":406,"height":365,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1582372510159.png" alt="" class="wp-image-486" width="406" height="365"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bloating is one of the most annoying stomach problems, familiar to many people around the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The description of this disease in people can vary, but the main concern is always the same including the feeling of increased pressure in the abdomen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It can be associated with many other stomach problems like irritable bowel syndrome, but it can happen independently after a heavy meal or with a poor diet.&nbsp;We are always trying to provide you with the best ways to maintain your health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, here are 10 ways to save yourself from bloating and its annoying pain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":488,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/wrong-check-symbols_1176-335.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-488"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can prevent bloating by eating more slowly and in smaller portions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you pay close attention to what you eat and pay attention to your food intake, this could help you better appreciate the food, as your brain will have time to process what you put in your mouth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, it will reduce the amount of air bubbles you swallow with your meal which is the disastrous cause of bloating in the first place.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This way of eating is called "mindful eating".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This means that you should think about your food intake as a way to treat your body well and not overdo it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Basically, conscious consumption consists in not hurrying so that you can enjoy your food, cook your own meals, hydrate your body, do not multitask and above all, respect your body and your health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":490,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/elevated-view-hand-holding-turnips-soil-desk_23-2148181207.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-490"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kale and broccoli are indeed nutrient-dense and fiber-rich vegetables that you need to eat to have a strong digestive system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, these foods are also rich in raffinose, which is a sugar that can only be digested by bacteria in your stomach and its fermentation is exactly what makes you swell.&nbsp;Try to keep the amount you eat and maybe the steam or broths may reduce the amount of sugar you take.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":492,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535b.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-492"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you continue to be swollen, you may want to watch your salt intake.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Eating foods high in sodium can slow body build up to get rid of excess water, which can make you feel like there''s a balloon in your stomach.&nbsp;You could digest a lot more sodium than ...</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>your stomach.&nbsp;You could digest much more sodium than recommended by the American Heart Association, that is, no more than 1500 mg per day for adults.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Salt is extremely difficult to avoid due to its presence in most processed and prepackaged foods.&nbsp;If you feel like you''ve failed your healthy, almost salt-free diet, drink more water to flush it out of your body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":494,"width":426,"height":282,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535c.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-494" width="426" height="282"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you''ve been abusive with salty foods, you could invest in bananas.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They prevent water from being trapped in your body due to sodium.&nbsp;Bananas are full of potassium and perfectly regulate salt levels to reduce bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meanwhile, the enzymes in papaya and pineapple also help break down proteins in your system, which wonderfully helps your stomach process food.&nbsp;So eat these fruits after a heavy meal to strengthen your digestive tract and help you avoid constipation and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a hearty meal, you may want to treat yourself to a cup of chamomile or peppermint tea.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":500,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535d.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-500"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both are known to relax spasms in your stomach and relieve your pain if you feel bloated.&nbsp;Chamomile tea not only helps digestion, but it can also relax and soothe you so you don''t pay as much attention to your belly problems.&nbsp;Peppermint oil is also available as a supplement if your cup of tea is not.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotic yogurt puts you out of bloating with its active cultures.&nbsp;As you probably know, there are millions of different bacteria found in your stomach and some of them can cause excess gas in your digestive tract.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Probiotics help regulate gas production and bloating if you are unlucky enough to suffer from it, and several studies have proven this.&nbsp;You can also take probiotic supplements instead of yogurt.&nbsp;If the yogurt is too sour for you, you can add honey or jam to sweeten this morning treat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":496,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535g.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-496"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you overeat and start to feel the annoying gas going up in your stomach, you can lie down and have someone do an abdominal massage for you, or you can do it yourself.&nbsp;This will help food move lower in your stomach and relieve tightness, excessive pressure and bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":497,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535h.png" alt="" class="wp-image-497"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most people don''t like the idea of ​​moving around after a meal.&nbsp;But if you have freed yourself and are experiencing the first symptoms of gas and acid reflux, do not take medication immediately.&nbsp;Just fifteen minutes of yoga can be as useful as a pill and it''s much healthier.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are several poses that can help relieve the tightness in your belly, helping your digestive tract to move food, stimulating your organs, and relieving the stress that partially causes bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":498,"width":417,"height":511,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/535i.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-498" width="417" height="511"/><figcaption>lireetpartager</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whatever the time, you should never forget to hydrate your body. Water is actually a solution to many of the health problems you may be having, and one of them is bloating. Your daily consumption of water is supposed to be around 8 glasses and that doesn''t even count the other liquids you drink. So stay hydrated and your body will have all the power it needs to fight bloating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '10 Solid Ways To Reduce Stomach Bloating.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-23 15:39:18', '2020-02-23 15:39:18', '', 474, 'https://en.2fun.club/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(519, 1, '2020-02-23 19:50:46', '2020-02-23 19:50:46', '<!-- wp:image {"id":373,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/scientific-medical-infographic-atherosclerosis_1308-32788.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-373"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  The leading cause of death in the world, according to the World Health Organization (WHO), cardiovascular disease is a group of disorders affecting the heart and blood vessels. Several factors lead to the appearance of these, such as smoking, physical inactivity, diabetes or even hyperlipidemia. To guard against cardiovascular disease, it is essential to adopt a healthy lifestyle and to favor foods that improve the health of the arteries. Here are 15 foods to include in your diet to protect against cardiovascular disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  Heart attacks, strokes, atherosclerosis, all of which can be life-threatening. The E-Times tells us that to avoid them, it is essential to have a healthy lifestyle by promoting exercise and foods that clean the arteries. Did you know that sardines are good for cardiovascular health? If you read the following lines, you will know what you need to incorporate into your diet to protect your arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1- Orange</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":444,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/sliced-whole-oranges_144627-3981.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-444"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Citrus is the ideal food for clearing arteries. It is full of pectins and thus blocks the absorption of bad cholesterol by the body. According to this study, frequent consumption of orange juice allows a considerable drop in the cholesterol present in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>2- kale</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":446,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/meal-vegetable-food-agriculture-vitamin_1203-5924.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-446"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Leafy vegetables are recommended for cleaning the arteries, especially kale. Rich in omega 3, antioxidants and fiber, this food should be preferred by people likely to develop arterial disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3- Spinach</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":448,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/top-view-bowl-salad-cloth_23-2148381242.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-448"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in vitamin A and C, spinach is also a great source of beta carotene. According to this study, this food is very effective in combating the stiffness of the arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4- pomegranate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":450,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/exotic-delicious-pomegranate-white-background_144627-12572.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-450"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This delicious fruit is effective in clearing the arteries. Rich in punic acid and antioxidants, it prevents plaque from forming inside the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: its consumption helps fight against all cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5- Sesame seeds</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":452,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/various-seeds-sesame-flax-seed-flax-seeds-pumpkin-seed-poppy-chia-bowls-rustic-copy_114579-3953.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-452"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> These seeds are ideal for combating the development of atherosclerosis. According to this study, their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory power acts as a real shield for the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6- Garlic</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":454,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unpeeled-garlic_144627-12048.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-454"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Renowned for many virtues, garlic is also effective in reducing plaque and blood pressure. According to the researchers, the food is useful in reducing the effects of atherosclerosis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7- Dark chocolate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":456,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/chocolate-dark-coffee-confiserie-65882.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-456"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its richness in cocoa and flavonoids, dark chocolate helps make the arteries more flexible and thus prevent heart disease. A small square per day is advisable to enjoy its benefits on overall health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8- Lemon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":458,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/lemon_1205-1668.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-458"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its powerful antioxidant power, lemon is excellent for the health of the arteries and the heart. The citrus fruit is also rich in vitamin C, helping to reduce inflammation and lower the cholesterol level in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9- Turmeric</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":460,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/turmeric-powder_1323-400.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-460"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The golden spice is effective in fighting atherosclerosis and lowering cholesterol levels in the blood. Rich in polyphenols, it helps protect the arteries and more generally the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10- Sardines</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":462,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-3650159.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-462"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in omega 3 and fatty acids, sardines are the most recommended fish for heart health. They increase levels of good cholesterol as well as reduce inflammation. According to this study, sardines help protect cardiovascular health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>11- Lentils</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":464,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pardina-lentils_1368-8865.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-464"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their richness in magnesium, potassium and proteins, lentils help to reduce the plaque present in the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: the consumption of these oilseeds is recommended for the heart.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>12- Almond</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":467,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/almonds_1339-237.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-467"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their antioxidant power, almonds are recommended for coronary health. According to the researchers, they lower the hyperlipidemia responsible for most cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>13- Watermelon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":469,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-1398655.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-469"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in citrulline, an amino acid, watermelon helps to heal inflammation and cleanse the arteries. This fruit is also rich in nitric oxide, an element that reduces blood pressure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>14- Blueberries</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":471,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/ripe-blueberry-green-leaves-cup_23-2148196308.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-471"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Blueberries are prized for their antioxidant action. They reduce the plaque responsible for atherosclerosis and fight against free radicals responsible for cardiovascular disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Caution :</strong><br> Before introducing these foods into your diet, it is essential to consult a specialist doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '14 foods you should eat to clean your arteries and keep them healthy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-23 19:50:46', '2020-02-23 19:50:46', '', 312, 'https://en.2fun.club/312-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(520, 1, '2020-02-24 17:31:36', '2020-02-24 17:31:36', '<!-- wp:image {"id":539,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1582568976230.png" alt="" class="wp-image-539"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our kidneys are vital for our body.&nbsp;They are located at the back of the abdomen and are in charge of many processes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Their main functions include detoxification and cleaning the system, as they filter our blood and produce urine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They also have a role in removing excess waste and fluids from the body, regulating blood pressure, increasing the number of red blood cells, balancing electrolytes, as well as supporting bone health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our whole body becomes at great risk if any of their function is compromised, so it is very important to know how to recognize the symptoms of kidney problems.&nbsp;Here we present you with a list of 8 signs that will tell us if our kidney function is threatened:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. FATIGUE</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":526,"width":357,"height":357,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/tired-businessman-character_1133-376.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-526" width="357" height="357"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Healthy kidneys produce erythropoietin.&nbsp;It is the hormone that increases the number of red blood cells.&nbsp;Fatigue as well as problems with the muscles and the brain are just a few of the problems that people with low red blood cells have.&nbsp;The same signs can be attributed to anemia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. PAIN</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":528,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/human-body-physical-injury-round-flat-set-with-shoulder-knee-finger-burn-cut-wounds-isolated_1284-27038.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-528"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pain in the area around the kidneys is a typical sign of kidney stones or urinary tract infections.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3. LOW CONCENTRATION AND DIZZINESS</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":530,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/view-thoughtful-young-caucasian-woman-dressed-pullove-seriously-focused_8353-10673.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-530"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Insufficient oxygen to the brain which leads to poor concentration, memory problems, and dizziness appear due to kidney failure and severe anemia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. THE METAL TASTE IN THE MOUTH</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When you have accumulated waste products in your blood, it changes the taste of your food and causes bad breath.&nbsp;Some of the major signs of kidney damage are the metallic taste in the mouth and lack of appetite.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. SHAVING THE SKIN</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":535,"width":387,"height":387,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/woman-shaving-legs_23-2147929835.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-535" width="387" height="387"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Skin rashes and itching may appear due to the buildup of waste products.&nbsp;As the waste builds up in the blood, the skin dries up and becomes irritated.&nbsp;This problem cannot be solved with creams and lotions because the root cause is internal and needs another approach.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6. DURATION OF BREATHING</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This symptom can appear because of the low number of red blood cells, caused by a toxic build-up in the lungs, because it reduces the amount of oxygen in the body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7. OIL</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":532,"width":420,"height":236,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/front-view-cup-with-olive-oil-table_23-2148285939.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-532" width="420" height="236"/><figcaption>Freepik</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The excess fluids remain trapped in the body and lead to swelling if kidney function is compromised.&nbsp;This swelling appears on the face, limbs and joints in particular.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8. CHANGES IN URINE</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are some of the most common signs:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Foamy<br>urine Urinary problems<br>Urination 