>\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just arrived in the stomach, some foods can hurt us: burns, nausea, and vomiting. Uncommon symptoms may also indicate indigestion, intolerance or food poisoning. Hence the interest of consulting a specialist to make the difference and make a precise diagnosis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Wheezing</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The allergen transported by the air, such as pollen or cat’s hair, is able to penetrate very far into the body. When it comes into contact with the bronchi of a predisposed person, they will close, like a spring, against the intruder: it is the bronchial spasm or asthma. As a result of this obstruction, the air tends to get stuck inside. Hence the need to force to expel the air. This respiratory discomfort causes shortness of breath and may result in whistling, which is produced by the passage of air through the narrowed bronchi. However, it should also be known that the first symptom of asthma, before whistling, is sometimes a dry cough.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Respiratory alert signs</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Signs of a severe crisis requiring emergency treatment? The person can not lie down and has the sensation of choking; his breathing becomes harder and harder, causing sweating, faster heart rate, and anxiety. Showing the drop in the amount of oxygen in the blood, fingers, and lips can cyanose and take a blue-violet color. Asthma can also result in permanent shortness of breath, on which crises can be added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'It is dangerous and should not be neglected related to allergies', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '413-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-02-24 20:52:32', '2020-02-24 20:52:32', '', 413, 'https://en.2fun.club/413-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(545, 1, '2020-02-25 13:01:04', '2020-02-25 13:01:04', '<!-- wp:image {"id":548,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1582638775845.png" alt="" class="wp-image-548"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to the ignorance of the symptoms, many Romanians come to the doctor with advanced forms of cancer that dramatically reduce their chances of survival.<br>Fever, fatigue, sudden weight loss, bloating, abdominal pain, but also cough that persist for long periods of time can "treat" many types of cancer.<br>Specialists highlight symptoms that should not be overlooked by both women and men.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Tiredness</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Above all, the ignored symptoms are fatigue, as it is not a specific cancer sign.&nbsp;"Fatigue is a symptom associated with cancer of all types and usually occurs due to anemia caused by it," explains oncologist Serban Negru.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>2. Weight loss</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unexplained weakness, without physical exertion or diet, may be a sign that the thyroid is very active.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>"If you do not change your diet and lifestyle and still lose weight, it means that, regardless of the type, the cancer is already installed," explains Dr. Serban Negru.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>3. Persistent cough</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cough can also announce the presence of cancer.&nbsp;Usually, it occurs in case of a cold, flu or allergy.&nbsp;An extended cough (lasting more than a month) should not be ignored.&nbsp;It can be caused by the irritation caused by such a malignant tumor, but it can also be a sign of lung disease, which is not cancer.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Therefore, specialists recommend that you go to the doctor for an examination of the neck, lungs, and an x-ray may be required for smokers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>4. Fever</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People who have a fever without the flu or other infection should go for a check.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the case of cancer patients, the fever occurs especially after the disease has spread in the body, but it may also be an early sign of leukemia or lymphoma.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>"Fever is a symptom that occurs very rarely and usually means associated overinfection for any type of cancer," says the oncologist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>5. Bloating and abdominal pain</strong><ins></ins></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bloating can be accompanied by abdominal and pelvic pain, feeling of satiety and urinary problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>"Pain is a symptom commonly associated with cancer.&nbsp;Please note that not all cancers are missed and it is possible to go for control too late, when the disease is already in metastasis or advanced stages ”, stresses the seriousness of the medical condition Serban Negru.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>6. Indigestion</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the indigestion does not have a good reason it can be considered an alarm signal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>"This symptom occurs especially in digestive cancers and can be very varied.&nbsp;From dysphagia (you cannot swallow) to esophageal cancer, to feeling of satiety, constipation, diarrhea, bleeding associated with the stool, ”details the oncologist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>7. Back pain</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the pancreatic duct is blocked by a tumor, the acid produced by the pancreas to aid in the digestion process returns and destroys the pancreas.&nbsp;This can cause abdominal pain that often radiates to the back.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To distinguish back muscle pain from one caused by a tumor in the pancreas, consider that the second type manifests intensely, persists and does not react to anti-inflammatory treatment.&nbsp;Also, the back pain caused by a tumor in the pancreas will cause another symptom: the stool loses its brown color, becoming discolored (like clay), and the urine becomes dark in color.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dr. Oz recommends leaning forward to make a distinction between the two types of back pain. The pain caused by a tumor in the pancreas disappears when you lean forward, while the muscle pain will persist.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Six symptoms of cancer that people ignore until it''s too late', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'six-symptoms-of-cancer-that-people-ignore-until-its-too-late', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=545', 0, 'post', '', 0),
