(554, 1, '2020-02-25 21:59:35', '2020-02-25 21:59:35', '<!-- wp:image {"id":557,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/maxresdefault-5-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-557"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A report by the American Heart Association and the American Stroke Association is sounding an alarm about too much of a common substance found in common, widely consumed foods.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Following the research, the experts concluded that we consumed approximately 3,400 milligrams of sodium daily, despite the recommended daily intake of 1,500 milligrams.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>National Healthy Eating Day has made a list of six foods that are high in sodium and should be consumed with great care.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1.&nbsp;Bread is the first food with a high salt content.&nbsp;A slice of bread contains about 15% of the daily recommended amount of salt.&nbsp;It is enough to eat a few slices of bread to pass immediately the recommended threshold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>2.&nbsp;Sausages are also part of the list of foods that should be consumed with measure.&nbsp;Parisian, prawns, salami are the most unhealthy because of the large amount of salt, but also of other ingredients.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A report by the National Authority for Consumer Protection, based on data from 2010, shows that&nbsp;especially the Parisian, the crickets and the summer salami have a protein content of 2% lower than the legal provisions, according to which the sausages must contain meat in proportion of at least 10-11%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, it is full of mechanically boned meat, ie a paste obtained from tendons, bones, skins, in which the proteins are almost non-existent.&nbsp;This is dangerous for children or young people, because of the high amount of phosphorus that prevents the assimilation of calcium.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>"If in the EU, the producers are not allowed to put more than 3% of this paste in sausages, in the Romanian products the quantity of MDM exceeds 10%",&nbsp;draws attention the food expert Gheorghe Mencinicopschi.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mice, known as collagen protein, are the basic ingredient of sausages.&nbsp;Although a limit of 20-30% is stipulated in the law, depending on the type of product, ANPC inspectors&nbsp;found products in which the quantity of pig skin was 80%.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The finding is all the more alarming as the Romanians consume 9-10 kg of sausages annually,&nbsp;mostly cheap products.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3.</strong>&nbsp;Pizza is one of the favorite dishes of people from all over the globe.&nbsp;Two slices of pizza cover the maximum amount of salt that can be consumed every day.<ins></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4.</strong>&nbsp;Chicken meat is one of the healthiest foods.&nbsp;The large amount of salt helps to keep products of this kind efficient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>5.</strong>&nbsp;Sandwiches are real salt bombs.&nbsp;In addition to the large amount of sodium found in bread, the foods that come to complete a perfect boil make it an extremely harmful combination for health.<br><br>It is good to know that excessive salt intake contributes to altered health and can cause serious heart disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'Five foods that make your heart sick. How often do you consume them?', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', '554-2', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=554', 0, 'post', '', 0),
