(561, 1, '2020-02-27 19:29:27', '2020-02-27 19:29:27', '<!-- wp:image {"id":564,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1582834070297.png" alt="" class="wp-image-564"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Certain more or less obvious signs can show that your cat is sick: change of behavior, drop in form or appetite ... It is still necessary to know how to detect them and what are the points to observe in the attitude and on your tomcat''s body.&nbsp;So we have put together ten common symptoms that could indicate a disease in cats and should be watched if in doubt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Your cat''s general health</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If your cat seems less active or more distant than usual, you must first be attentive to his general health and his physical appearance: is he moving normally? Does he sleep more? Are they showing signs of apathy and fatigue? Sleep is an important indicator, so any change in rhythm should alert you even if the cat is an animal that sleeps a lot by nature. During his waking periods, pay attention to his attitude: does he have his head down? Does he play and eat as before? Is it coming to you? This criterion is important because a sick animal prefers to isolate itself.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Weight loss and appetite</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":566,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/cat-food-1024x682.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-566"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These two symptoms usually go hand in hand, but not always! Indeed, certain pathologies can make the cat lose weight even if he does not eat less than usual. If in doubt, your cat''s eating behavior should be closely monitored as well as its water consumption. Refusal to eat, quibbling or any change in eating habits should lead you to consult the veterinarian.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Excessive cravings should also alarm you, as should dehydration. You can check by gently pulling and releasing the skin on your cat''s neck: if it doesn''t come back quickly, it means it''s dehydrated. Finally, to control the weight of your animal, weigh it regularly between veterinary visits.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Detecting fever in cats</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most reliable method to know the temperature of your cat is to take his rectal temperature using a thermometer: it must be between 38 ° and 39 ° C. If it is higher than 39 ° C, this means that he has a fever.&nbsp;Get help because he will surely not let it go!&nbsp;To prevent it from scratching and biting, wrap it in a towel and hold its head.&nbsp;Please note, if its temperature is below 38 ° C, your cat is hypothermic which is a very bad sign.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Check your cat''s coat</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":568,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/depositphotos_4460181-stock-photo-long-haired-cat-being-brushed.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-568"/><figcaption> depositphotos</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The appearance of the coat is an important factor in judging the good health of your cat.&nbsp;Dirty, stuck, greasy, dull or peeled hair can be a sign of illness.&nbsp;Thoroughly inspect its fur for crusts or parasites (fleas, ticks).&nbsp;Other dermatological symptoms such as hair loss, redness, irritation, itching can testify to the presence of invisible parasites such as scabies or ringworm.&nbsp;If you notice a growth or lump under the skin, consult the veterinarian to check that they are not tumors or abscesses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Watch your cat''s eyes</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The color of the mucous membranes and the appearance of the third eyelid are crucial indicators of disease in cats.&nbsp;Her eyes should not run or look damp or glassy, ​​or have crusts or dirt on their corners.&nbsp;Swollen, yellow, grayish or red dot-dyed mucous membranes should alert you, which could indicate pathology or intoxication.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Auscultate your cat''s mouth</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like the color of the mucous membranes, an abnormal color of the gums is a sign of a potentially serious illness.&nbsp;Lift your cat''s lips and watch your teeth and gums for abscesses or blood bags.&nbsp;This may explain eating difficulties or even a complete refusal to eat due to the pain caused by a condition of the mouth and teeth.&nbsp;The tongue may also have small pimples, abscesses, a puffy appearance or an unusual color.&nbsp;Bad breath can be a witness to dental but also digestive problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Changes in cat behavior</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":570,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/post_5c218f002a3c3-1024x682.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-570"/><figcaption>kot-pes</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to monitoring the physical appearance of your cat, be attentive to its behavior and observe its changes in habits and mood.&nbsp;Sudden aggression, irritability, restlessness, distant behavior can show that he is suffering.&nbsp;If he is stressed, claws when you touch him or does not let himself be approached, it is because something is wrong.&nbsp;Unusual mews or, on the contrary, mutism in a normally "talkative" cat are also sometimes indicators.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Monitor cat''s stool and urine condition</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The digestive symptoms are particularly important to know if your cat is sick: diarrhea, change of habit with the litter box, abundant or difficult urination, needs made in the house ... If you have any doubt about his health, have the reflex to check his stools: if they are smaller, harder, softer than usual or show traces of blood, consult the veterinarian.&nbsp;It is possible that it is infested with worms or suffers from inflammation of the intestine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Vomiting in cats</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is normal for a cat to regurgitate from time to time because of the hair it swallows while washing.&nbsp;However, repeated and painful vomiting is a sign of illness, indigestion, food poisoning or poisoning.&nbsp;You should therefore consult quickly to rule out these possibilities, since the ingestion of toxic products or foods requires immediate intervention.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Respiratory symptoms of the cat</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Respiratory conditions such as coryza cause difficulty breathing, resulting in a rapid, jerky rhythm, coughing, and sneezing. Breathing can then be accompanied by wheezing and snoring. Pulmonary edema, asthma, pneumonia, laryngitis and many other respiratory conditions can affect the cat. Immediate consultation is therefore recommended since they can lead to serious complications.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', 'How do I know if my cat is sick? 10 symptoms to watch for', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-know-if-my-cat-is-sick-10-symptoms-to-watch-for', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=561', 0, 'post', '', 0),
