(592, 1, '2020-03-08 16:06:18', '2020-03-08 16:06:18', '<!-- wp:image {"id":606,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1583686653041.png" alt="" class="wp-image-606"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unexplained fatigue, blurred mind, extra pounds and hair loss are all signs of a thyroid gland problem.&nbsp;The same is true for the opposite symptoms: sweating and anxiety.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This "regulator" of the body and mind sometimes goes crazy, especially in the case of women.&nbsp;Proper treatment is extremely important for maintaining health and avoiding serious problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It produces hormones that control the speed of metabolism.&nbsp;Thyroid disorders can slow or revitalize metabolism by inhibiting thyroid hormone production.&nbsp;When your hormone level is too low or too high, a wide range of symptoms may occur.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Tiredness</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":596,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/pexels-photo-3786636.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-596"/><figcaption>Prxels</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you feel tired for no reason: do not work hard, sleep more than 6 hours a night, eat properly - then guilt may be thyroid.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A deficiency of thyroid function - hypothyroidism - can lead to a decrease in thyroid hormones, which leads to a "slowdown" of the entire metabolism, of the function of most organs in the body, including the brain.&nbsp;The patient experiences an unexplained fatigue, it is difficult to even get up to get a cup of water, physical activities become difficult, etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. Changes in memory and mental state</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A hypothyroid becomes depressive, thinks hard, forgets and remembers with difficulty certain information, basically the brain functions "slacken".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the case of a hyperthyroid, the brain functions are "worse", the patient tends to euphoria, but quickly passes from one idea to another, forget what he spoke 5 seconds ago, he has a sharp and unsteady mind.&nbsp;He sleeps less and is overactive.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>3. Changes in sexual function and menstruation</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":599,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/desperate-2048905__480.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-599"/><figcaption>Pixabay</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Changes in sexual function in both men and women may also be due to thyroid disorders: libido disorder, erection, infertility.&nbsp;Also, menstrual disorders in women may have a thyroid pathology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. Feeling of choking and palpitations</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Palpitations can often be accompanied by the sensation of suffocation.&nbsp;The affected person feels the beating of the heart as being strong, fast and at the same time has a "thirst for air".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These manifestations may occur in several pathologies, including hyperthyroidism or thyroid cancer with hyperthyroid manifestations - excess thyroid hormones.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The effects of hyperthyroidism can be very serious in a seizure, with cardiac arrhythmia, atrial fibrillation, which is difficult to respond to and can culminate in death.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. Changes in the skin</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the skin becomes rougher, it thickens, is matte, lacks vitality, dry and cold - possibly hypothyroidism;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the skin becomes moist, thin, soft, soft to the touch ("baby-like"), warm - possibly hyperthyroidism</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>6. Digestive disorders</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":601,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ezgif-6-dcbfc32214d2-790x1024.png" alt="" class="wp-image-601"/><figcaption>Pixabay</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Severe constipation is commonly associated with hypothyroidism, and diarrhea and irritable bowel syndrome are specific to hyperthyroidism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>7. Muscle and joint pain</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sensations of pain in the muscles and joints and the feeling of weakness of the arms may be indications of the poor functioning of the thyroid gland.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>8. Hypertension</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Both hypothyroidism and hyperthyroidism cause increased blood pressure.&nbsp;According to estimates, people with hypothyroidism have a risk of hypertension 2-3 times higher.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>9. Changes in body temperature</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thyroid disorders can affect the ability to adjust body temperature.&nbsp;People with hypothyroidism will be colder than normal.&nbsp;Hyperthyroidism has the opposite effect, causing excessive sweating.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>10. Thickening of the voice</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is possible that the patient concerned did not notice the change of voice, but those around can notice this change.&nbsp;If the voice changes, especially by thickening the vocal stamp, it is most likely hypothyroid.&nbsp;Also the thinning of the voice, easy to see especially in the case of a man, may suggest a thyroid pathology - hyperthyroidism - but also another local or endocrine disease in the larynx.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>11. Abrupt Weight Change</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most common symptoms that suggest a thyroid gland problem is sudden weight change.&nbsp;Weight gain indicates a low level of thyroid gland hormones, which is called hypothyroidism.&nbsp;At the opposite pole, if the thyroid produces more hormones than the body needs, there will be a sudden drop in weight, which is called hyperthyroidism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>12. Excessive hair loss</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":603,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ezgif-6-3cd952a0a6b3.png" alt="" class="wp-image-603"/><figcaption>Pixabay</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hair loss can be physiological in various cases such as stress, change of season, change of diet, intense sports, excessive use of hair care products and hairstyles etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But if this hair loss lasts for more than two weeks, it continues to appear when you stop using cosmetics for your hair - you should consult your dermatologist.&nbsp;You may have a scalp infection, a vitamin D or ferritin deficiency (iron deposits decrease or you are anemic), you have an infection, or you have an endocrine disorder (thyroid, ovary).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Analyzes are recommended for the detection of the above pathologies, including anti-thyroid hyperoxidase (ATPO) antibodies for a possible autoimmune thyroiditis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>13. Discomfort and anatomical changes in the neck</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have a feeling that your neck is swollen or you even notice anatomic changes at this level (goose), accompanied by changes of voice, ask for emergency medical check-up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;<strong>Treatment of hypothyroidism</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are diagnosed with hypothyroidism, your doctor will prescribe you hormones in the form of pills, and your health will be noticed within a few weeks.&nbsp;Most people with hypothyroidism will have to take hormones for the rest of their lives.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Treatment of hyperthyroidism</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most common treatment for hyperthyroidism is the administration of anti-thyroid drugs, which aim to reduce the amount of hormones produced by the thyroid gland.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Surgery for thyroid disorders</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Elimination of the thyroid gland can cure hyperthyroidism, but the procedure is recommended only if the drugs do not work or if the patient has a large mouth.&nbsp;Surgery may also be recommended in patients with thyroid nodules.&nbsp;Once the thyroid is eliminated, most patients require daily thyroid hormone supplements to prevent the development of hypothyroidism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Thyroid cancer</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thyroid cancer is rarely encountered and is among the least dangerous types of cancer. The main symptom is a lump or swelling of the neck. Only 5% of thyroid nodules turn out to be cancerous.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '13 warning signs that the thyroid is not functioning properly', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'warning-signs-that-the-thyroid-is-not-functioning-properly', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=592', 0, 'post', '', 0),
