p:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>10. Thickening of the voice</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is possible that the patient concerned did not notice the change of voice, but those around can notice this change.&nbsp;If the voice changes, especially by thickening the vocal stamp, it is most likely hypothyroid.&nbsp;Also the thinning of the voice, easy to see especially in the case of a man, may suggest a thyroid pathology - hyperthyroidism - but also another local or endocrine disease in the larynx.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>11. Abrupt Weight Change</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the most common symptoms that suggest a thyroid gland problem is sudden weight change.&nbsp;Weight gain indicates a low level of thyroid gland hormones, which is called hypothyroidism.&nbsp;At the opposite pole, if the thyroid produces more hormones than the body needs, there will be a sudden drop in weight, which is called hyperthyroidism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>12. Excessive hair loss</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":603,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/ezgif-6-3cd952a0a6b3.png" alt="" class="wp-image-603"/><figcaption>Pixabay</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hair loss can be physiological in various cases such as stress, change of season, change of diet, intense sports, excessive use of hair care products and hairstyles etc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But if this hair loss lasts for more than two weeks, it continues to appear when you stop using cosmetics for your hair - you should consult your dermatologist.&nbsp;You may have a scalp infection, a vitamin D or ferritin deficiency (iron deposits decrease or you are anemic), you have an infection, or you have an endocrine disorder (thyroid, ovary).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Analyzes are recommended for the detection of the above pathologies, including anti-thyroid hyperoxidase (ATPO) antibodies for a possible autoimmune thyroiditis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>13. Discomfort and anatomical changes in the neck</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you have a feeling that your neck is swollen or you even notice anatomic changes at this level (goose), accompanied by changes of voice, ask for emergency medical check-up.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>&nbsp;<strong>Treatment of hypothyroidism</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are diagnosed with hypothyroidism, your doctor will prescribe you hormones in the form of pills, and your health will be noticed within a few weeks.&nbsp;Most people with hypothyroidism will have to take hormones for the rest of their lives.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Treatment of hyperthyroidism</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most common treatment for hyperthyroidism is the administration of anti-thyroid drugs, which aim to reduce the amount of hormones produced by the thyroid gland.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Surgery for thyroid disorders</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Elimination of the thyroid gland can cure hyperthyroidism, but the procedure is recommended only if the drugs do not work or if the patient has a large mouth.&nbsp;Surgery may also be recommended in patients with thyroid nodules.&nbsp;Once the thyroid is eliminated, most patients require daily thyroid hormone supplements to prevent the development of hypothyroidism.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><strong>Thyroid cancer</strong></h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thyroid cancer is rarely encountered and is among the least dangerous types of cancer.&nbsp;The main symptom is a lump or swelling of the neck.&nbsp;Only 5% of thyroid nodules turn out to be cancerous.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '592-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-08 15:25:13', '2020-03-08 15:25:13', '', 592, 'https://en.2fun.club/592-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
