(706, 1, '2020-03-18 18:21:42', '2020-03-18 18:21:42', '<!-- wp:image {"id":705,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1584559064159.png" alt="" class="wp-image-705"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  The leading cause of death in the world, according to the World Health Organization (WHO), cardiovascular disease is a group of disorders affecting the heart and blood vessels. Several factors lead to the appearance of these, such as smoking, physical inactivity, diabetes or even hyperlipidemia. To guard against cardiovascular disease, it is essential to adopt a healthy lifestyle and to favor foods that improve the health of the arteries. Here are 15 foods to include in your diet to protect against cardiovascular disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>  Heart attacks, strokes, atherosclerosis, all of which can be life-threatening. The E-Times tells us that to avoid them, it is essential to have a healthy lifestyle by promoting exercise and foods that clean the arteries. Did you know that sardines are good for cardiovascular health? If you read the following lines, you will know what you need to incorporate into your diet to protect your arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1- Orange</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":444,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/sliced-whole-oranges_144627-3981.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-444"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Citrus is the ideal food for clearing arteries. It is full of pectins and thus blocks the absorption of bad cholesterol by the body. According to this study, frequent consumption of orange juice allows a considerable drop in the cholesterol present in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>2- kale</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":446,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/meal-vegetable-food-agriculture-vitamin_1203-5924.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-446"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Leafy vegetables are recommended for cleaning the arteries, especially kale. Rich in omega 3, antioxidants and fiber, this food should be preferred by people likely to develop arterial disorders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3- Spinach</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":448,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/top-view-bowl-salad-cloth_23-2148381242.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-448"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in vitamin A and C, spinach is also a great source of beta carotene. According to this study, this food is very effective in combating the stiffness of the arteries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4- pomegranate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":450,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/exotic-delicious-pomegranate-white-background_144627-12572.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-450"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> This delicious fruit is effective in clearing the arteries. Rich in punic acid and antioxidants, it prevents plaque from forming inside the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: its consumption helps fight against all cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5- Sesame seeds</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":452,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/various-seeds-sesame-flax-seed-flax-seeds-pumpkin-seed-poppy-chia-bowls-rustic-copy_114579-3953.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-452"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> These seeds are ideal for combating the development of atherosclerosis. According to this study, their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory power acts as a real shield for the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6- Garlic</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":454,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unpeeled-garlic_144627-12048.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-454"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Renowned for many virtues, garlic is also effective in reducing plaque and blood pressure. According to the researchers, the food is useful in reducing the effects of atherosclerosis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7- Dark chocolate</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":456,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/chocolate-dark-coffee-confiserie-65882.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-456"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its richness in cocoa and flavonoids, dark chocolate helps make the arteries more flexible and thus prevent heart disease. A small square per day is advisable to enjoy its benefits on overall health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8- Lemon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":458,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/lemon_1205-1668.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-458"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to its powerful antioxidant power, lemon is excellent for the health of the arteries and the heart. The citrus fruit is also rich in vitamin C, helping to reduce inflammation and lower the cholesterol level in the blood.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9- Turmeric</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":460,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/turmeric-powder_1323-400.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-460"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The golden spice is effective in fighting atherosclerosis and lowering cholesterol levels in the blood. Rich in polyphenols, it helps protect the arteries and more generally the cardiovascular system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10- Sardines</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":462,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-3650159.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-462"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in omega 3 and fatty acids, sardines are the most recommended fish for heart health. They increase levels of good cholesterol as well as reduce inflammation. According to this study, sardines help protect cardiovascular health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>11- Lentils</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":464,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pardina-lentils_1368-8865.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-464"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their richness in magnesium, potassium and proteins, lentils help to reduce the plaque present in the arteries. It''s scientifically proven: the consumption of these oilseeds is recommended for the heart.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>12- Almond</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":467,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/almonds_1339-237.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-467"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Thanks to their antioxidant power, almonds are recommended for coronary health. According to the researchers, they lower the hyperlipidemia responsible for most cardiovascular diseases.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>13- Watermelon</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":469,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/pexels-photo-1398655.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-469"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Rich in citrulline, an amino acid, watermelon helps to heal inflammation and cleanse the arteries. This fruit is also rich in nitric oxide, an element that reduces blood pressure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>14- Blueberries</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":471,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/ripe-blueberry-green-leaves-cup_23-2148196308.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-471"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Blueberries are prized for their antioxidant action. They reduce the plaque responsible for atherosclerosis and fight against free radicals responsible for cardiovascular disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Caution :</strong><br> Before introducing these foods into your diet, it is essential to consult a specialist doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '14 foods you should eat to clean your arteries and keep them healthy', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '312-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-18 18:21:42', '2020-03-18 18:21:42', '', 312, 'https://en.2fun.club/312-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(707, 1, '2020-03-19 00:22:13', '2020-03-19 00:22:13', '<!-- wp:image {"id":732,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1584580465824.png" alt="" class="wp-image-732"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>   Every day our minds process a lot of information, our body performs thousands of actions. Living in this busy world is very easy to miss a few messages your body sends. And the consequences of not communicating and responding to these signals can be drastic</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> I made a list of signs that indicate that the kidneys are not functioning properly. How many of these signals did your body send you?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1) Changes in the urine</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":721,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/645928E8-30A0-4FE2-9001-E45E8FF34724.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-721"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The kidneys are responsible for producing urine and eliminating waste through it. Frequent changes, odor, color and appearance of urine should not be ignored. Common patterns of change include:<br> Increased need for urination, especially at night. Anything between 4 to 10 times a day is considered normal. Blood in the urine. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Healthy kidneys remove waste from the blood to produce urine, but if the filter is damaged, blood cells may begin to "pass" into the urine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Foamy urine. Urine foam, especially those that ask you to wash several times before leaving, indicates that unwanted protein is in the urine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2) High blood pressure</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The circulatory system and the kidneys depend on each other. The kidneys have small nephrons, which filter out waste and extra fluid from the blood. If the blood vessels are damaged, the nephrons that filter the blood do not receive enough oxygen and nutrients. Therefore, high blood pressure is the second leading cause of kidney failure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Tip: Learn how to manage high blood pressure to avoid kidney failure. Add foods rich in folic acid because it is involved in the production of red blood cells and can help prevent anemia.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3) Cearcane</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":722,"width":382,"height":382,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/8D0ADB0D-2E51-4990-8AAD-4B30E2944CB9.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-722" width="382" height="382"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> An early sign that your kidney filtration system is damaged is the onset of protein in the urine, which can lead to clogging around the eye area. The swelling around the eye can be explained by the fact that the kidneys release a large amount of protein into the urine, instead of keeping it and distributing it throughout the body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Tip: If you are sure that your body is getting enough rest and protein, but you will still notice circles around your eyes, make sure to schedule an appointment to visit your doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4) Back pain</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Kidney failure can lead to back pain, usually deep. It can be felt in the front of the groin area or the hip Back and foot pain can be caused by kidney cysts, which are large, fluid-filled sacs that are the result of polycystic kidney disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Tip: Back pain caused by kidney failure is accompanied by feeling sick, vomiting, high body temperature and frequent urination. Normal back pain that does not correlate with the kidneys behaves differently the pain is more localized and occurs suddenly, there is no fever. If you experience back pain and pain relief pills are ineffective, make sure you see your doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5) Swelling of the ankles, feet and hands</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":724,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/A91538D8-8F4D-4501-893B-739BDE65D6FF.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-724"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Kidneys that fail to function properly do not remove the extra fluid from the body. This results in sodium retention which causes swelling of the ankles, feet and hands. Swelling of the lower parts of the body can also signal heart and liver problems or vein problems in the legs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: Sometimes taking medications, reducing salt and removing excess fluid from your body can stop the sweling. If it doesn''t help, then you need a separate treatment</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>6) Shortness of breath</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":725,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/E28AA781-BA14-4749-AF07-99163A1F921C.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-725"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The relationship between kidney disease and breathing difficulties, especially after a small effort, is caused by two factors. First, the extra fluid in the body moves into the lungs when the kidneys are not functioning properly. Secondly, anemia will deprive the body of oxygen and this will shorten the breath.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: There are several reasons to shorten your breath from kidney failure to asthma and lung cancer or heart failure. If you notice that you are permanently out of breath after making very little effort, you should contact your doctor immediately.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>7) Experience bad breath and metallic taste</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":726,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/D2F65655-5620-4197-9D91-B98705686098.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-726"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When waste accumulates in the blood, they change the taste of food and leave a metallic taste in the mouth. Having bad breath is another sign of having too many toxins and contamination in the blood. In addition, you may no longer want meat and lose your appetite in general, which can lead to unhealthy weight loss.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: There are various reasons why foods may taste metallic (from allergies to poor oral health). Normally, the metallic taste in the mouth should disappear if the alleged cause has been treated. If the taste continues to appear, you should contact your doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:nextpage -->\n<!--nextpage-->\n<!-- /wp:nextpage -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>8) With dry skin and itching</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":727,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/115221C6-EAED-4687-A85E-F4A7F6F2569E.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-727"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Healthy kidneys do an extraordinary job by eliminating waste and extra fluid from the blood, helping to produce red blood cells and maintaining the proper amount of minerals in your body. Dry skin signals kidney failure to maintain the proper balance of minerals and nutrients that can lead to osteoporosis and kidney disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: If you have dry skin and itching, try to stay more hydrated. Remember, before taking any itching medicine consult your doctor. Certain drugs have ingredients that could affect kidney function even more</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9) Headaches, fatigue and general weakness</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":728,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/06348528-5747-43EE-BD86-3D01CECA6ADE.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-728"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Healthy, well-functioning kidneys convert vitamin D into our body to maintain strong bones and produce a hormone called erythropoietin (EPO). This hormone plays an important role in the production of red blood cells. When the kidneys are not functioning properly, they produce less EPO. The decline of red blood cells (those carrying oxygen) leads to rapid fatigue of the muscles and brain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: People with chronic kidney disease are accustomed to anemia. Anemia may start to develop when someone has 20% to 50% of normal kidney function. If you relax enough and sleep, but continue to feel fatigue, low energy and general weakness, you should consult your doctor without delay</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10) Problems with sleep</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":729,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1102.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-729"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> When the kidneys are not functioning properly, it means that the toxins cannot exit the body through the urine and remain in the blood. Increasing the level of toxins makes it difficult to fall asleep. Therefore, when you sleep less, your chances of decreasing kidney function increase.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: People with chronic kidney disease often suffer from sleep apnea. Sleep apnea is a disorder that causes one or more breaks in your breathing when you sleep. These breaks can take from a few seconds to a minute. After each pause, normal breathing returns with a loud noise. Continuous snoring syndrome indicates that it is time to visit a doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '10 signs that your kidneys are not functioning properly', '', 'private', 'open', 'open', '', 'signs-that-your-kidneys-are-not-functioning-properly', '', '', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '2020-03-28 14:01:27', '', 0, 'https://en.2fun.club/?p=707', 0, 'post', '', 0),
