ng</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":727,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/115221C6-EAED-4687-A85E-F4A7F6F2569E.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-727"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Healthy kidneys do an extraordinary job by eliminating waste and extra fluid from the blood, helping to produce red blood cells and maintaining the proper amount of minerals in your body. Dry skin signals kidney failure to maintain the proper balance of minerals and nutrients that can lead to osteoporosis and kidney disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="4"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: If you have dry skin and itching, try to stay more hydrated. Remember, before taking any itching medicine consult your doctor. Certain drugs have ingredients that could affect kidney function even more</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>9) Headaches, fatigue and general weakness</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":728,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/06348528-5747-43EE-BD86-3D01CECA6ADE.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-728"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Healthy, well-functioning kidneys convert vitamin D into our body to maintain strong bones and produce a hormone called erythropoietin (EPO). This hormone plays an important role in the production of red blood cells. When the kidneys are not functioning properly, they produce less EPO. The decline of red blood cells (those carrying oxygen) leads to rapid fatigue of the muscles and brain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: People with chronic kidney disease are accustomed to anemia. Anemia may start to develop when someone has 20% to 50% of normal kidney function. If you relax enough and sleep, but continue to feel fatigue, low energy and general weakness, you should consult your doctor without delay</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>10) Problems with sleep</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":729,"sizeSlug":"large"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://en.2fun.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/1102.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-729"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> When the kidneys are not functioning properly, it means that the toxins cannot exit the body through the urine and remain in the blood. Increasing the level of toxins makes it difficult to fall asleep. Therefore, when you sleep less, your chances of decreasing kidney function increase.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Warning: People with chronic kidney disease often suffer from sleep apnea. Sleep apnea is a disorder that causes one or more breaks in your breathing when you sleep. These breaks can take from a few seconds to a minute. After each pause, normal breathing returns with a loud noise. Continuous snoring syndrome indicates that it is time to visit a doctor.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[adinserter block="3"]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->', '10 signs that your kidneys are not functioning properly', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '707-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-03-19 00:21:53', '2020-03-19 00:21:53', '', 707, 'https://en.2fun.club/707-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
