(847, 1, '2020-04-02 18:09:10', '2020-04-02 18:09:10', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are always ways to make good training even better and more effective.&nbsp;The following tips ensure optimal training results.&nbsp;Get the best out of your training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, even bodybuilding beginners should know that variation is one of the most important factors for sustained progress in muscle building and strength gain.&nbsp;If you carry out the same training plan with the same variables (exercise sequence, number of sets, number of repetitions) over and over again without major changes, this ultimately leads to stagnation and a lack of further muscle building.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This does not mean that you have to constantly change your training plan completely.&nbsp;If you integrate the following tips into the training, you will quickly find that you are making progress again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Do not follow a certain number of repetitions.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are still many bodybuilders who do 3 sets of 10 reps by default on almost all exercises.&nbsp;They come to the studio, choose a weight for the bench press, for example, with which they can definitely do 10 repetitions.&nbsp;You do a set, then a pause, the next 10 repetitions, pause and a third time.&nbsp;After a few months, they are amazed that they are no longer making progress in terms of muscle building and strength gain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '846-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-02 18:09:10', '2020-04-02 18:09:10', '', 846, 'https://en.2fun.club/846-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(848, 1, '2020-04-02 18:10:51', '2020-04-02 18:10:51', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are always ways to make good training even better and more effective.&nbsp;The following tips ensure optimal training results.&nbsp;Get the best out of your training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, even bodybuilding beginners should know that variation is one of the most important factors for sustained progress in muscle building and strength gain.&nbsp;If you carry out the same training plan with the same variables (exercise sequence, number of sets, number of repetitions) over and over again without major changes, this ultimately leads to stagnation and a lack of further muscle building.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This does not mean that you have to constantly change your training plan completely.&nbsp;If you integrate the following tips into the training, you will quickly find that you are making progress again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Do not follow a certain number of repetitions.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are still many bodybuilders who do 3 sets of 10 reps by default on almost all exercises. They come to the studio, choose a weight for the bench press, for example, with which they can definitely do 10 repetitions. You do a set, then a pause, the next 10 repetitions, pause and a third time. After a few months, they are amazed that they are no longer making progress in terms of muscle building and strength gain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The problem with that;&nbsp;the body has enough time to get used to the strain.&nbsp;If you continue training with 10 repetitions and can easily do them in each of the 3 sets, you will ensure that the body and muscles can adjust to the load.&nbsp;Then there are no further signs of adaptation, the training stimulus for the muscles is not high enough for further muscle building.&nbsp;In theory, you can train for years without any noteworthy progress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead of aiming for the typical 10 repetitions after the warm-up set, you should instead choose higher weights that only allow repetitions between 6-8.&nbsp;Especially at the beginning of the training when the energy levels are still high.&nbsp;Sets with repetitions between 8-10 can then be performed later in the training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you would like to continue training with 10 reps, you should definitely choose the weight so that you are just 10 reps.&nbsp;can create.&nbsp;If you are 10Wdh.&nbsp;can do without having to deflect the movement or need help, then you should definitely take more weight.&nbsp;This tip mainly applies to multi-joint exercises such as bench press, lat pulldown, squat, neck press and the training goal of building muscle and gaining strength.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '846-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-02 18:10:51', '2020-04-02 18:10:51', '', 846, 'https://en.2fun.club/846-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(850, 1, '2020-04-02 18:20:04', '2020-04-02 18:20:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are always ways to make good training even better and more effective.&nbsp;The following tips ensure optimal training results.&nbsp;Get the best out of your training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, even bodybuilding beginners should know that variation is one of the most important factors for sustained progress in muscle building and strength gain.&nbsp;If you carry out the same training plan with the same variables (exercise sequence, number of sets, number of repetitions) over and over again without major changes, this ultimately leads to stagnation and a lack of further muscle building.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This does not mean that you have to constantly change your training plan completely.&nbsp;If you integrate the following tips into the training, you will quickly find that you are making progress again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Do not follow a certain number of repetitions.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are still many bodybuilders who do 3 sets of 10 reps by default on almost all exercises.&nbsp;They come to the studio, choose a weight for the bench press, for example, with which they can definitely do 10 repetitions.&nbsp;You do a set, then a pause, the next 10 repetitions, pause and a third time.&nbsp;After a few months, they are amazed that they are no longer making progress in terms of muscle building and strength gain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The problem with that;&nbsp;the body has enough time to get used to the strain.&nbsp;If you continue training with 10 repetitions and can easily do them in each of the 3 sets, you will ensure that the body and muscles can adjust to the load.&nbsp;Then there are no further signs of adaptation, the training stimulus for the muscles is not high enough for further muscle building.&nbsp;In theory, you can train for years without any noteworthy progress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead of aiming for the typical 10 repetitions after the warm-up set, you should instead choose higher weights that only allow repetitions between 6-8.&nbsp;Especially at the beginning of the training when the energy levels are still high.&nbsp;Sets with repetitions between 8-10 can then be performed later in the training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you would like to continue training with 10 reps, you should definitely choose the weight so that you are just 10 reps. can create. If you are 10Wdh. can do without having to deflect the movement or need help, then you should definitely take more weight. This tip mainly applies to multi-joint exercises such as bench press, lat pulldown, squat, neck press and the training goal of building muscle and gaining strength.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. If possible, schedule your Monday training on a Sunday.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As you have probably already noticed, Monday is the worst day for training, especially if you are one of the many who want to train chest on Monday.&nbsp;So even if you prefer to watch the sports show on Sunday or plan other activities, Sunday is a great day for a workout.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If all the benches for your breast training are occupied on a Monday, the studio on Sunday is usually super empty.&nbsp;Bodybuilders at a higher level therefore often train on Sundays in order to be able to carry out their training plan even without unwanted breaks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3. Install small cardio sessions in the breaks between sets.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a rule, many athletes use the breaks between sets for a small small talk with training partners or a nice girl, share selfies on Facebook / Instagram or simply dream away.&nbsp;Cardio training is still waiting for most athletes, especially in the definition phase, at the end of regular strength training.&nbsp;W</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So is there any argument against integrating cardio training into the strength training unit so that your stay in the studio is shorter and the training becomes more effective?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So instead of chatting with the girls, or squeezing your butt flat between sets on a bench, you can speed things up, train your cardiovascular system and burn calories, all at the same time.&nbsp;Active relaxation in the form of moderate cardio training between sets ensures more productive training and significantly shortens the time spent in the studio.&nbsp;During breaks you can use the stepper, jump rope or do box jumps for about a minute each.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Those who incorporate rapid cardio training as active relaxation into their training 1-2 times a week increase their overall performance, since the balance, footwork, overall strength and muscle endurance improve significantly within just a few weeks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. Use smaller weights on the barbell.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From a certain training level, it makes sense to train with a training partner.&nbsp;In order to achieve an optimal growth stimulus for the muscles, one has to train until the load is stopped.&nbsp;With many exercises, this is not possible without a training partner.&nbsp;But since the weight range in which you train is often quite different, it makes sense to find a convenient way to exchange weights between the training sets of both athletes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is definitely wasted energy if you have to constantly change 20kg discs.&nbsp;If you use smaller weight plates such as 5, 10 or 15 kg plates, the training weights can be converted more easily, which saves time and energy.&nbsp;This variant is also positive for dropsets, as you can gradually remove the small slices from the barbell and thus make the dropsets finely graded.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. Use pulling aids for a few extra repetitions.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You have certainly experienced it more often;&nbsp;when back training on the lat machine or also with standard pull-ups, the grip fails earlier than the back muscles.&nbsp;However, it is counterproductive for optimal muscle development or for strength gain if the back cannot be properly trained due to the decreasing holding power of the hands.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you feel that your grip is weakening, use a few pulling aids and you will be able to do a few more repetitions per set, which in turn will help you build more muscle.&nbsp;Grip strength shouldn''t be the limiting factor on your back day.&nbsp;If you want to train the forearm muscles in order to strengthen the grip strength, you should include exercises for the forearm muscles at the end of the bicep training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you use pulling aids, you should ensure that the latissimus can be trained in isolation and that the pulling aids take over the holding work.&nbsp;The advantage is that you don''t have to choose an excessively firm grip even with very heavy weights.&nbsp;The forearms are protected and the focus is on the back, which can be optimally trained.&nbsp;But that doesn''t mean that you should only train with pulling aids, even with the lighter sets.&nbsp;It makes sense to train part of the exercise without pulling aids so that the grip and forearm muscles are also trained.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '846-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-02 18:20:04', '2020-04-02 18:20:04', '', 846, 'https://en.2fun.club/846-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(849, 1, '2020-04-02 18:12:08', '2020-04-02 18:12:08', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are always ways to make good training even better and more effective.&nbsp;The following tips ensure optimal training results.&nbsp;Get the best out of your training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nowadays, even bodybuilding beginners should know that variation is one of the most important factors for sustained progress in muscle building and strength gain.&nbsp;If you carry out the same training plan with the same variables (exercise sequence, number of sets, number of repetitions) over and over again without major changes, this ultimately leads to stagnation and a lack of further muscle building.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This does not mean that you have to constantly change your training plan completely.&nbsp;If you integrate the following tips into the training, you will quickly find that you are making progress again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>1. Do not follow a certain number of repetitions.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are still many bodybuilders who do 3 sets of 10 reps by default on almost all exercises.&nbsp;They come to the studio, choose a weight for the bench press, for example, with which they can definitely do 10 repetitions.&nbsp;You do a set, then a pause, the next 10 repetitions, pause and a third time.&nbsp;After a few months, they are amazed that they are no longer making progress in terms of muscle building and strength gain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The problem with that;&nbsp;the body has enough time to get used to the strain.&nbsp;If you continue training with 10 repetitions and can easily do them in each of the 3 sets, you will ensure that the body and muscles can adjust to the load.&nbsp;Then there are no further signs of adaptation, the training stimulus for the muscles is not high enough for further muscle building.&nbsp;In theory, you can train for years without any noteworthy progress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead of aiming for the typical 10 repetitions after the warm-up set, you should instead choose higher weights that only allow repetitions between 6-8.&nbsp;Especially at the beginning of the training when the energy levels are still high.&nbsp;Sets with repetitions between 8-10 can then be performed later in the training.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you would like to continue training with 10 reps, you should definitely choose the weight so that you are just 10 reps. can create. If you are 10Wdh. can do without having to deflect the movement or need help, then you should definitely take more weight. This tip mainly applies to multi-joint exercises such as bench press, lat pulldown, squat, neck press and the training goal of building muscle and gaining strength.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>2. Lege Dein Montagstraining wenn möglich auf einen Sonntag.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wie Du wahrscheinlich schon mitbekommen hast, ist der Montag der schlechteste Tag für das Training, speziell wenn Du auch zu den vielen gehörst, die am Montag Brust trainieren wollen. Also auch wenn Du am Sonntag lieber die Sportschau guckst oder andere Aktivitäten planst, für ein Training ist der Sonntag ein super Tag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wenn an einem Montag alle Bänke für Dein Brusttraining besetzt sind, so ist das Studio am Sonntag in der Regel super leer. Bodybuilder auf einem höheren Level trainieren daher oft sonntags, um ihren Trainingsplan auch ohne ungewollte Pausen durchziehen zu können.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>3. Baue kleine Cardioeinheiten in den Pausen zwischen den Sätzen ein.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In der Regel nutzen viele Sportler die Pausen zwischen den Sätzen für einen kleinen Smalltalk mit Trainingspartnern oder einem netten Mädel, teilen Selfies auf Facebook/Instagram oder träumen einfach vor sich hin. Gerade in der Definitionsphase wartet aber auf die meisten Sportler noch das Cardiotraining, am Ende des regulären Krafttrainings. W</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>as spricht also dagegen, dass Cardiotraining schon in die Krafttrainingseinheit zu integrieren, damit der Aufenthalt im Studio kürzer und das Training effektiver wird?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Anstatt also mit den Mädels zu schnacken, oder den Hintern zwischen den Sätzen auf einer Bank platt zu drücken, kann man die Dinge beschleunigen, dass Herz-/Kreislaufsystem trainieren und Kalorien verbrennen, alles zur selben Zeit. Eine aktive Erholung in Form eines moderaten Cardiotrainings zwischen den Sätzen, sorgt für ein produktiveres Training und verkürzt die Aufenthaltszeit im Studio deutlich. Du kannst in den Pausen den Stepper nutzen, Seil springen oder Box Jumps jeweils für ca. eine Minute machen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wer 1-2x wöchentlich in sein Training ein schnelles Cardiotraining als aktive Erholung einbaut, der steigert seine allgemeine Leistungsfähigkeit, da sich die Balance, die Fußarbeit, die Gesamtkraft und Muskelausdauer innerhalb von nur ein paar Wochen deutlich verbessert.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>4. Verwende eher kleinere Gewichtsscheiben auf der Hantelstange.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ab einem gewissen Trainingslevel ist es sinnvoll, mit einem Trainingspartner zu trainieren. Um einen optimalen Wachstumsreiz für die Muskulatur zu erreichen, muss man bis zum Belastungsabbruch trainieren. Bei vielen Übungen ist das gefahrlos nicht ohne Trainingspartner möglich. Da aber oft der Gewichtsbereich in dem trainiert wird, ziemlich unterschiedlich ist, macht es Sinn einen bequemen Weg zu finden, wie man zwischen den Trainingssätzen beider Sportler die Gewichte tauschen kann.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Es ist auf jeden Fall verschwendete Energie, wenn man ständig 20kg Scheiben wechseln muss. Wenn man kleinere Gewichtsscheiben wie 5, 10 oder 15kg Scheiben nutzt, dann können die Trainingsgewichte leichter umgebaut werden, was Zeit und Kraft spart. Positiv ist diese Variante auch bei Dropsets, da man nach und nach die kleinen Scheiben von der Hantel nehmen kann und so die Dropsets fein abgestuft machen kann.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>5. Nutze Zughilfen für ein paar extra Wiederholungen.</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Du hast es sicherlich auch schon häufiger erlebt; beim Rückentraining an der Latmaschine oder auch bei Standard Klimmzügen, versagt der Griff früher als die Rückenmuskulatur. Es ist aber kontraproduktiv für eine optimale Muskelentwicklung oder auch für den Kraftzuwachs, wenn der Rücken aufgrund nachlassender Haltekraft der Hände, nicht richtig austrainiert werden kann.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wenn Du merkst, dass Dein Griff nachlässt, dann nutze ein paar Zughilfen und Du bist in der Lage, ein paar Wiederholungen pro Satz mehr zu machen, was wiederum für einen stärkeren Muskelaufbau sorgt. Die Griffkraft sollte nicht der limitierende Faktor an Deinem Rückentag sein. Wer gezielt die Unterarmmuskulatur trainieren will, um die Griffkraft zu stärken, der sollte Übungen für die Unterarmmuskulatur am Ende des Bizepstrainings mit einbauen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wer Zughilfen einsetzt, der sollte sicher stellen, dass der Latissimus isoliert trainiert werden kann und die Zughilfen die Haltearbeit übernehmen. Der Vorteil ist, man muss auch bei sehr schweren Gewichten keinen übermäßig festen Griff wählen. Die Unterarme werden geschont und der Fokus liegt auf dem Rücken, der so optimal austrainiert werden kann. Das heißt jetzt aber nicht, dass man nur noch mit Zughilfen trainieren sollte, auch bei den leichteren Sätzen. Es macht schon Sinn, auch einen Teil der Übung ohne Zughilfen zu trainieren, damit der Griff und die Unterarmmuskulatur auch noch mittrainiert werden.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '846-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-04-02 18:12:08', '2020-04-02 18:12:08', '', 846, 'https://en.2fun.club/846-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
